251
00:15:43.240 --> 00:15:45.520
Yeah. Yeah. maybe.

252
00:15:45.600 --> 00:15:46.920
Rugby's good. but

253
00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:49.560
you should have something
outside of school just for you.

254
00:15:49.640 --> 00:15:52.960
Maybe then you'll start to realize
how great you are.

255
00:15:55.640 --> 00:15:57.480
[school bell rings]

256
00:16:05.440 --> 00:16:07.640
Hey. You okay?

257
00:16:10.040 --> 00:16:12.240
Did you wanna talk to me about something?

258
00:16:14.200 --> 00:16:16.160
[intriguing music playing]

259
00:16:18.840 --> 00:16:21.960
[Charlie] Growing up queer can be
so isolating and scary.

260
00:16:22.800 --> 00:16:24.960
Especially in a single-sex school.

261
00:16:25.760 --> 00:16:29.520
You're an easy target for bullies.
You might struggle to make friends.

262
00:16:29.600 --> 00:16:33.520
Queer kids need a space they feel
supported by older students and teachers.

263
00:16:34.120 --> 00:16:37.320
The thing is. Charlie.
it sets a precedent.

264
00:16:37.840 --> 00:16:41.280
We don't have any other clubs
for… social groups.

265
00:16:41.360 --> 00:16:43.280
Well. maybe this could be the first.

266
00:16:44.320 --> 00:16:47.000
I don't think I can commit to this
right now. Charlie.

267
00:16:47.880 --> 00:16:50.840
Let's wait a few months.
and we'll revisit.

268
00:16:53.520 --> 00:16:54.520
♪ Yeah ♪

269
00:16:56.200 --> 00:16:57.200
♪ Hey ♪

270
00:16:58.000 --> 00:16:59.000
♪ Yeah… ♪

271
00:16:59.680 --> 00:17:01.240
He's got a mustache. [chuckles]

272
00:17:04.080 --> 00:17:06.000
[Michael] I'm training
with a new coach up north.

273
00:17:06.040 --> 00:17:10.560
Also teaching kids how to skate.
which is endlessly entertaining.

274
00:17:10.640 --> 00:17:13.640
He won't say it. but he's training
to qualify for the Winter Olympics.

275
00:17:13.720 --> 00:17:15.080
Wait. are you serious?

276
00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:17.960
There's more to it.
but. yeah. that's the general idea.

277
00:17:18.040 --> 00:17:20.160
-So you're just back for the weekend?
-[Michael] Yeah.

278
00:17:20.240 --> 00:17:23.080
I mean. three months
without seeing Tori. so…

279
00:17:23.160 --> 00:17:26.040
-Yeah. sounds rough.
-[Michael] I mean. we're okay though.

280
00:17:26.120 --> 00:17:28.000
I mean. there's…
there's her life and my life.

281
00:17:28.080 --> 00:17:32.640
and when we're together. it's…
it's like… [whooshing. mimics explosion]

282
00:17:33.680 --> 00:17:36.000
But when we're apart. it's like…

283
00:17:36.080 --> 00:17:39.080
Whoo… [mimics explosion]

284
00:17:39.160 --> 00:17:41.400
Also. phones exist. so…

285
00:17:41.480 --> 00:17:42.920
[Charlie chuckles softly]

286
00:17:46.200 --> 00:17:48.680
[Nick] I think you need to finish this
'cause I'm struggling.

287
00:17:48.760 --> 00:17:50.360
Wait. if you hold the end. I can…

288
00:17:51.640 --> 00:17:53.520
[pensive music playing]

289
00:17:53.600 --> 00:17:55.800
[Nick breathing quickly]

290
00:18:02.680 --> 00:18:03.680
Hey.

291
00:18:04.360 --> 00:18:05.960
Hey. what's up? What's going on?

292
00:18:10.600 --> 00:18:12.480
[Nick breathes shakily]

293
00:18:12.560 --> 00:18:14.360
I had a dream you died.

294
00:18:15.200 --> 00:18:16.200
[Charlie] What?

295
00:18:18.560 --> 00:18:19.720
[Nick gasps]

296
00:18:20.680 --> 00:18:21.960
Sorry. I…

297
00:18:23.680 --> 00:18:27.600
It's so stupid. I just…
It felt really real. [sniffles]

298
00:18:28.960 --> 00:18:29.960
Sorry.

299
00:18:30.760 --> 00:18:32.760
-It's okay.
-[breathing heavily]

300
00:18:32.840 --> 00:18:35.200
It's not real. I'm right here.

301
00:18:43.760 --> 00:18:45.120
-[Charlie] Can you…
-[Nick] Got it.

302
00:18:45.160 --> 00:18:46.200
[Charlie] Thank you.

303
00:18:46.280 --> 00:18:48.040
[Tao] I'll take that.

304
00:18:48.120 --> 00:18:49.920
-[Darcy] I'll get that.
-[Charlie] Great.

305
00:18:52.840 --> 00:18:54.880
[indistinct chattering]

306
00:18:54.960 --> 00:18:57.320
All right. Santa Claus is coming to town.

307
00:18:57.400 --> 00:19:00.320
-[Elle] Yes. please.
-[Isaac] You look a bit like him.

308
00:19:00.400 --> 00:19:04.160
Everyone say cheers and thank you to Nick
for being able to legally buy alcohol.

309
00:19:04.240 --> 00:19:06.680
I know that's the only reason
you keep me around.

310
00:19:06.760 --> 00:19:08.160
[Imogen] Oh. don't say that.

311
00:19:08.240 --> 00:19:09.680
Charlie looks fit.

312
00:19:10.760 --> 00:19:13.280
It's the self-confidence.
It's transformative.

313
00:19:13.880 --> 00:19:16.240
I think when you know yourself.
it's really powerful.

314
00:19:16.320 --> 00:19:20.640
-Speaking of. I wanted to...
-Okay. everybody. we are Queer Intentions.

315
00:19:20.720 --> 00:19:22.200
-[cheering]
-Whoo! Whoo-whoo!

316
00:19:22.280 --> 00:19:25.640
We're here to play you some music tonight.
so who's ready to rock?

317
00:19:25.720 --> 00:19:27.280
I'm ready! I'm ready!

318
00:19:28.880 --> 00:19:31.520
[band playing
"I Only Want to Be With You"]

319
00:19:31.600 --> 00:19:33.640
-Who's dancing?
-[Nick] I like this one.

320
00:19:33.720 --> 00:19:35.440
-[Tara] Let's dance.
-What. already?

321
00:19:35.520 --> 00:19:38.080
-Yes. Come on. Nicholas!
-I've just got… Wait.

322
00:19:38.160 --> 00:19:39.440
[Tara whooping]

323
00:19:39.520 --> 00:19:43.280
♪ I only know I never wanna let you go ♪

324
00:19:43.360 --> 00:19:47.240
♪ 'Cause you started something
Oh. can't you see ♪

325
00:19:47.320 --> 00:19:50.840
♪ That ever since we met
You've had a hold on me? ♪

326
00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:54.280
♪ It happens to be true ♪

327
00:19:54.360 --> 00:19:58.120
♪ I only wanna be with you ♪

328
00:19:58.640 --> 00:20:00.960
♪ You stopped to smile at me… ♪

329
00:20:01.040 --> 00:20:02.080
Yeah. Charlie!

330
00:20:02.160 --> 00:20:05.640
[Sahar] ♪ Asked me if I'd care to dance ♪

331
00:20:05.720 --> 00:20:09.280
♪ I fell into your open arms ♪

332
00:20:09.360 --> 00:20:13.400
♪ I didn't stand a chance ♪

333
00:20:13.480 --> 00:20:17.640
♪ Now listen. honey
I just wanna be beside you everywhere… ♪

334
00:20:17.720 --> 00:20:20.480
-Go on. Charlie!
-[Christian] Nick! Hey. Nick. Tequila!

335
00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:22.720
-[Nick] Ah…
-Sort him out. Sort him out.

336
00:20:22.800 --> 00:20:24.000
-Here. bro.
-Okay.

337
00:20:24.080 --> 00:20:24.920
-You ready?
-Yep.

338
00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:27.120
-Right. Everyone.
-Right.

339
00:20:27.200 --> 00:20:29.120
-Cheers.
-[others] Cheers.

340
00:20:31.280 --> 00:20:32.360
-[boy coughs]
-Oh my…

341
00:20:33.080 --> 00:20:37.080
♪ I only wanna be with you ♪

342
00:20:37.160 --> 00:20:38.360
-I'm okay.
-Let's go again.

343
00:20:38.440 --> 00:20:40.040
-No. I'm okay.
-Come on!

344
00:20:40.120 --> 00:20:42.840
Please. Come on. One more.

345
00:20:43.960 --> 00:20:45.760
-[Sai] Come on.
-All right. okay.

346
00:20:45.840 --> 00:20:46.880
-You ready?
-Yeah.

347
00:20:46.960 --> 00:20:47.960
Right.

348
00:20:48.320 --> 00:20:50.560
-And cheers. boys.
-Cheers.

349
00:20:52.560 --> 00:20:57.280
♪ Now listen. honey
I just want to be beside you everywhere ♪

350
00:20:57.360 --> 00:21:01.080
♪ As long as we're together
Honey. I don't care ♪

351
00:21:01.160 --> 00:21:04.760
♪ 'Cause you've started something
Oh. can't you see ♪

352
00:21:04.840 --> 00:21:08.400
♪ That ever since we met
You've got a hold on me? ♪

353
00:21:08.480 --> 00:21:11.840
♪ No matter what you do ♪

354
00:21:11.920 --> 00:21:15.800
-♪ I only wanna be with you ♪
-[Christian] Yeah!

355
00:21:15.880 --> 00:21:19.080
[Sahar] ♪ No matter what you do ♪

356
00:21:19.160 --> 00:21:22.960
♪ I only. only. only. only ♪

357
00:21:23.040 --> 00:21:26.840
♪ I only wanna be with you ♪

358
00:21:26.920 --> 00:21:28.840
[cheering]

359
00:21:28.920 --> 00:21:31.320
One more song! One more song!

360
00:21:31.400 --> 00:21:33.480
Um. so we have got another song for you.

361
00:21:33.560 --> 00:21:36.640
It's a Christmas song
'cause the manager says we have to.

362
00:21:36.720 --> 00:21:38.640
But you might recognize this one.

363
00:21:38.720 --> 00:21:43.240
-[a cappella] ♪ Deck the halls with… ♪
-Oh. I love this one.

364
00:21:45.160 --> 00:21:48.440
♪ 'Tis the season to be jolly… ♪

365
00:21:48.520 --> 00:21:49.600
[girl] Have we met?

366
00:21:49.680 --> 00:21:53.360
Yeah. I think. uh. I think we maybe went
to drama school together. Yeah.

367
00:21:53.440 --> 00:21:56.240
-Nice to meet you.
-♪ Don we now our gay apparel… ♪

368
00:21:56.320 --> 00:21:57.920
The band is so good.

369
00:21:58.000 --> 00:22:00.400
Yeah. Yeah.
That's… that's actually my boyfriend.

370
00:22:00.480 --> 00:22:01.800
Oh. hi.

371
00:22:04.360 --> 00:22:10.000
-[band plays rock version]
-♪ See the blazing yule before us ♪

372
00:22:10.520 --> 00:22:15.160
♪ Strike the harp and join the chorus ♪

373
00:22:16.320 --> 00:22:19.280
♪ Fast away the old year passes ♪

374
00:22:19.360 --> 00:22:22.360
[all] ♪ Fa la la la. la la la ♪

375
00:22:22.440 --> 00:22:25.280
[Sahar] ♪ Hail the new year
Lads and lasses ♪

376
00:22:25.360 --> 00:22:28.120
[all] ♪ Fa la la la. la la la ♪

377
00:22:28.200 --> 00:22:31.400
♪ Sing we joyous all together ♪

378
00:22:31.480 --> 00:22:34.280
[all] ♪ Fa la la la. la la la ♪

379
00:22:34.360 --> 00:22:37.320
[Sahar] ♪ Heedless of the wind
And weather ♪

380
00:22:37.400 --> 00:22:40.200
[all] ♪ Fa la la la. la la la… ♪

381
00:22:40.280 --> 00:22:44.400
-I love you! Oh!
-♪ See the blazing yule before us ♪

382
00:22:46.080 --> 00:22:49.600
-♪ Strike the harp and join the chorus ♪
-[Nick giggling]

383
00:22:49.680 --> 00:22:52.280
[all] ♪ Fa la la la la. la la la la ♪

384
00:22:52.360 --> 00:22:58.240
-[Sahar] ♪ Follow me in merry measure ♪
-[all] ♪ Fa la la la la la. la la la ♪

385
00:22:58.320 --> 00:22:59.520
[Sahar] ♪ While I tell ♪

386
00:22:59.600 --> 00:23:01.280
-♪ Of Yuletide treasure ♪
-Whoo!

387
00:23:01.360 --> 00:23:03.160
[urinating]

388
00:23:03.240 --> 00:23:04.880
[sighs]

389
00:23:05.400 --> 00:23:08.360
[toilet flushing]

390
00:23:08.440 --> 00:23:09.600
[zipper closing]

391
00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:13.120
[sniffs]

392
00:23:15.280 --> 00:23:17.800
[faucet running]

393
00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:27.880
[indistinct chattering]

394
00:23:34.720 --> 00:23:37.600
[Elle] It's like you don't even care
about my dreams.

395
00:23:37.680 --> 00:23:41.040
[Tao] I respect your dreams.
but not coming to visit me at all?

396
00:23:41.120 --> 00:23:44.360
I mean. Berlin's not even that far.
It's two hours by plane.

397
00:23:44.440 --> 00:23:46.440
I don't know what you want me to say. Tao.

398
00:23:46.520 --> 00:23:49.760
I'm sorry I'm not rich and have money
to get on a flight every two min...

399
00:23:49.840 --> 00:23:53.880
Hey. hey. hey. hey. You need to talk
to each other. Like. communicate.

400
00:23:53.960 --> 00:23:59.040
It's… it's just about communicating
and. and. and saying what's in there.

401
00:23:59.120 --> 00:24:02.560
That's… that's all that matters.
and then you'll be able to connect...

402
00:24:02.640 --> 00:24:04.000
Yeah. okay. Nick.

403
00:24:04.080 --> 00:24:06.240
No. if you love each other. it's easy.

404
00:24:06.320 --> 00:24:08.600
You know. me and Charlie.
we love each other...

405
00:24:08.680 --> 00:24:11.520
Yeah. we get it.
You and Charlie are perfect. all right?

406
00:24:12.040 --> 00:24:14.760
It's… it's just not the time
right now. Nick.

407
00:24:16.920 --> 00:24:17.920
All right.

408
00:24:20.800 --> 00:24:23.840
You guys were so good.

409
00:24:23.920 --> 00:24:26.640
Um. I've always wanted to learn
how to play the drums.

410
00:24:26.720 --> 00:24:29.080
-Oh. well. you… you still could.
-Yeah…

411
00:24:29.160 --> 00:24:31.720
It just… it seems so hard.
though. you know?

412
00:24:33.160 --> 00:24:34.680
Any drumming advice?

413
00:24:34.760 --> 00:24:35.760
[Charlie chuckles]

414
00:24:36.720 --> 00:24:38.360
Just… just practice.

415
00:24:38.440 --> 00:24:40.400
[last orders bell rings in distance]

416
00:24:40.480 --> 00:24:42.640
Hey. you all right?

417
00:24:43.520 --> 00:24:46.440
Charlie was just giving me
some drumming tips.

418
00:24:46.520 --> 00:24:50.440
Really? 'Cause it looks like
you were just flirting with my boyfriend.

419
00:24:50.520 --> 00:24:52.960
Well. we were just having
a conversation. so…

420
00:24:53.040 --> 00:24:55.720
Okay. well. conversation's over.

421
00:24:57.040 --> 00:24:58.040
Nick!

422
00:24:58.960 --> 00:25:01.480
-Nick. are you okay?
-He was flirting with you. so…

423
00:25:01.560 --> 00:25:03.640
Yeah. I know he was. I can handle myself.

424
00:25:03.720 --> 00:25:06.600
I didn't march over when that girl
was flirting with you earlier. did I?

425
00:25:06.680 --> 00:25:08.400
No. but that's different. isn't it?

426
00:25:08.920 --> 00:25:11.520
-Tao. can we just talk. please?
-[Tao] No. I don't want to.

427
00:25:11.600 --> 00:25:13.696
-[Elle] We can figure this out.
-[Tao] Nothing to say.

428
00:25:13.720 --> 00:25:16.840
-I'm gonna get another drink.
-[Charlie] No. You've had enough.

429
00:25:16.920 --> 00:25:18.280
Nick. [sighs]

430
00:25:19.280 --> 00:25:21.720
Hey. I'm going home. Is he okay?

431
00:25:21.800 --> 00:25:24.240
-Yeah. he's all right. I think.
-Hey. I'm glad.

432
00:25:24.320 --> 00:25:27.320
-[Nick] Another pint of lager. please.
-Sorry. mate. the bar's closed.

433
00:25:28.680 --> 00:25:29.680
Shit.

434
00:25:33.120 --> 00:25:35.880
-I think everyone hates me.
-[sighs] Let's get you home.

435
00:25:37.760 --> 00:25:39.920
-Are you angry at me?
-No. I'm not. Come on.

436
00:25:40.000 --> 00:25:42.400
-Sure?
-I'm not angry. I…

437
00:25:42.920 --> 00:25:44.880
Let's just get an Uber or something.

438
00:25:45.800 --> 00:25:47.480
What the fuck is wrong with him?

439
00:25:48.920 --> 00:25:50.280
I need to get him home.

440
00:25:51.560 --> 00:25:53.560
Throw up in the car and I'll kill you.

441
00:25:53.640 --> 00:25:55.360
[car keys jangling]

442
00:25:56.160 --> 00:25:57.200
Come on.

443
00:25:58.400 --> 00:26:00.800
[Nick breathes heavily. groans softly]

444
00:26:00.880 --> 00:26:02.520
[door opens. closes]

445
00:26:02.600 --> 00:26:04.400
Nick. open the door. [knocking]

446
00:26:05.080 --> 00:26:06.800
[Nick retching]

447
00:26:07.320 --> 00:26:09.960
-[Nick retching]
-[David scoffs softly]

448
00:26:10.040 --> 00:26:13.120
-[Nick groans] I'm fine.
-No. you're not. Let me in.

449
00:26:14.400 --> 00:26:18.480
Charlie. it's not nice. okay?
You don't wanna be in here.

450
00:26:18.560 --> 00:26:19.680
Yes. I do.

451
00:26:20.280 --> 00:26:21.840
I don't care. Let me help you.

452
00:26:21.920 --> 00:26:23.520
[yells] I don't need your help!

453
00:26:25.880 --> 00:26:27.520
[breathes heavily]

454
00:26:28.840 --> 00:26:29.840
Nick. let me in.

455
00:26:30.440 --> 00:26:31.440
[Nick sighs]

456
00:26:33.680 --> 00:26:36.600
[groans. grunts]

457
00:26:36.680 --> 00:26:38.680
[toilet flushing]

458
00:26:39.440 --> 00:26:40.480
[Nick] Sorry.

459
00:26:41.920 --> 00:26:43.160
[Charlie] What happened?

460
00:26:43.240 --> 00:26:45.320
[pensive music playing]

461
00:26:45.400 --> 00:26:47.680
[sighs] I don't know. I just…

462
00:26:49.320 --> 00:26:50.800
I got really drunk.

463
00:26:52.240 --> 00:26:55.320
[breathes shakily] The lads
kept giving me loads of shots.

464
00:26:55.400 --> 00:26:59.920
and… and I saw that guy flirting with you.
and I just…

465
00:27:01.520 --> 00:27:03.320
I went crazy. [sighs]

466
00:27:04.560 --> 00:27:05.800
[Charlie] But why?

467
00:27:07.080 --> 00:27:09.200
You know nothing would ever happen.

468
00:27:09.760 --> 00:27:12.840
[Nick inhales. exhales deeply]

469
00:27:12.920 --> 00:27:14.720
[Charlie] Let's talk about it tomorrow.

470
00:27:15.600 --> 00:27:18.880
[exhales slowly] I love knowing
that we have tomorrow.

471
00:27:24.000 --> 00:27:25.120
[Charlie sighs]

472
00:27:39.560 --> 00:27:40.880
[music fades]

473
00:27:53.000 --> 00:27:54.760
[sizzling in distance]

474
00:27:54.840 --> 00:27:56.440
[cookware clattering]

475
00:27:58.720 --> 00:28:02.480
I thought you'd wanna sleep in.
You were so pissed last night.

476
00:28:02.560 --> 00:28:06.440
[Nick] Yeah. [sighs]
I threw up again. like. half an hour ago.

477
00:28:06.520 --> 00:28:09.320
-Not a great sign for the match today.
-Hmm.

478
00:28:10.920 --> 00:28:13.320
[Nick] The pancakes are a "sorry"
for last night.

479
00:28:15.400 --> 00:28:16.680
You didn't have to do that.

480
00:28:16.760 --> 00:28:19.400
Well. I am. 'cause I was a mess.

481
00:28:20.800 --> 00:28:22.400
I've never seen you like that.

482
00:28:23.080 --> 00:28:26.080
It was funny at first. but then it wasn't.

483
00:28:28.680 --> 00:28:30.120
I'm worried about you.

484
00:28:30.640 --> 00:28:31.640
[Nick sighs]

485
00:28:32.520 --> 00:28:33.720
I'm all good.

486
00:28:37.120 --> 00:28:38.880
Right. I think these are nearly done.

487
00:28:39.400 --> 00:28:41.480
I don't think I can do pancakes today.

488
00:28:43.200 --> 00:28:45.200
-Are you not feeling good. or…
-I don't know.

489
00:28:45.280 --> 00:28:47.760
Is that why you keep forgetting
your lunch at school?

490
00:28:47.840 --> 00:28:49.040
No. I…

491
00:28:50.800 --> 00:28:52.160
I don't know. I'm…

492
00:28:53.640 --> 00:28:54.760
I'm gonna go shower.

493
00:28:55.360 --> 00:28:58.680
-Charlie. you can talk to me. you know.
-Why can't you talk to me?

494
00:28:58.760 --> 00:29:00.200
About what?

495
00:29:00.280 --> 00:29:04.080
Whatever it is that's making you feel
so anxious. I wanna support you.

496
00:29:04.160 --> 00:29:07.200
Okay. you don't need to use
your therapy speak on me. It's fine.

497
00:29:09.960 --> 00:29:11.240
-I'm going home.
-No. wait. I...

498
00:29:11.320 --> 00:29:14.480
When you actually wanna talk to me.
I'll be there. Okay?

499
00:29:16.800 --> 00:29:19.200
Can you just please eat something
when you get home?

500
00:29:20.240 --> 00:29:21.160
[Charlie scoffs]

501
00:29:21.240 --> 00:29:22.720
[melancholy music playing]

502
00:29:22.800 --> 00:29:24.720
[smoke alarm beeping]

503
00:29:24.840 --> 00:29:26.440
[Nick] Oh shit.

504
00:29:29.200 --> 00:29:30.240
[door closes]

505
00:29:30.320 --> 00:29:31.640
[pan hissing]

506
00:29:42.040 --> 00:29:44.480
-Thought you were at Nick's?
-Yeah. I was.

507
00:29:45.760 --> 00:29:46.760
[Tori] Toast?

508
00:29:51.360 --> 00:29:52.280
[boy 1] Come on!

509
00:29:52.360 --> 00:29:53.440
[girl 1] Go. go!

510
00:29:53.520 --> 00:29:55.320
[indistinct shouting. chattering]

511
00:29:59.080 --> 00:30:01.320
[boy 2] Go on. Nick! Go on. Nick!

512
00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:04.000
-[spectators cheering]
-[whistle blows]

513
00:30:04.880 --> 00:30:06.400
-[boy 1] Yeah.
-[Nick breathes heavily]

514
00:30:06.440 --> 00:30:08.160
-[Singh] Well done. Nick!
-[boy 3] Nice one.

515
00:30:12.120 --> 00:30:14.040
[Nick exhales. sniffs. sighs]

516
00:30:14.120 --> 00:30:17.720
[Geoff] I know you know it's normal
to have bad days and bad weeks.

517
00:30:17.800 --> 00:30:20.160
but excess stress
can certainly trigger them.

518
00:30:20.680 --> 00:30:24.000
Have you been dealing
with any additional stress lately?

519
00:30:24.080 --> 00:30:26.360
-[rugby players chattering]
-[whistle blows]

520
00:30:27.640 --> 00:30:28.840
[boy 3] On the wing!

521
00:30:30.160 --> 00:30:31.440
-[Nick grunts]
-[boy 4] Foul!

522
00:30:31.960 --> 00:30:32.960
[boy 5] Dickhead!

523
00:30:33.040 --> 00:30:36.320
I thought after all this.
I'd at least know how to help people.

524
00:30:36.400 --> 00:30:37.760
[uneasy music playing]

525
00:30:37.840 --> 00:30:39.640
What's the point of it otherwise?

526
00:30:40.280 --> 00:30:43.600
Are you referring to your head boy duties
or something else?

527
00:30:44.760 --> 00:30:45.760
[Charlie sighs]

528
00:30:46.320 --> 00:30:48.320
[Nick breathing heavily]

529
00:30:48.400 --> 00:30:49.400
[boy 6] Come on.

530
00:30:53.400 --> 00:30:55.120
I'm so worried about Nick.

531
00:30:55.200 --> 00:30:56.560
[uneasy music building]

532
00:30:57.440 --> 00:30:59.160
[rugby players shouting indistinctly]

533
00:31:01.800 --> 00:31:04.080
-[Nick grunting]
-[boy 6 grunts]

534
00:31:06.280 --> 00:31:07.960
-[boy 7] He started it!
-[Nick grunts]

535
00:31:08.040 --> 00:31:09.200
-[boy 6 grunts]
-[Nick groans]

536
00:31:09.240 --> 00:31:10.680
[boys shouting]

537
00:31:11.280 --> 00:31:14.600
-[boy 8] Are you all right?
-[boy 9] Someone get a teacher. man.

538
00:31:14.680 --> 00:31:16.760
-Look at me.
-[heartbeat pounding]

539
00:31:16.840 --> 00:31:17.840
[boy 9] You okay?

540
00:31:19.520 --> 00:31:22.640
[woman over PA] Dr. Walters.
please come to ward 24. Thank you.

541
00:31:22.720 --> 00:31:24.920
That's Dr. Walters to ward 24.

542
00:31:49.000 --> 00:31:50.040
[door opens]

543
00:31:50.880 --> 00:31:51.880
Oh!

544
00:31:52.360 --> 00:31:53.480
Silly boy.

545
00:31:53.560 --> 00:31:55.560
-Hey. Mum.
-Hi. Sarah.

546
00:31:57.040 --> 00:31:58.800
Silly. silly boy.

547
00:31:59.640 --> 00:32:01.480
Yeah. I probably shouldn't have…

548
00:32:02.880 --> 00:32:04.480
No. probably not.

549
00:32:04.560 --> 00:32:06.320
[pensive music playing]

550
00:32:08.400 --> 00:32:09.720
[Nick sighs]

551
00:32:11.000 --> 00:32:12.080
[Sarah sighs]

552
00:32:12.560 --> 00:32:13.560
Here.

553
00:32:14.120 --> 00:32:15.760
You look like a wounded soldier.

554
00:32:17.280 --> 00:32:19.640
Nice of Charlie to wait at the hospital.

555
00:32:21.360 --> 00:32:22.480
Yeah.

556
00:32:24.240 --> 00:32:25.920
Oh dear. What's happened?

557
00:32:27.760 --> 00:32:29.200
Uh. we had an argument.

558
00:32:30.040 --> 00:32:32.360
Which was my fault.

559
00:32:34.120 --> 00:32:36.320
You haven't really been yourself lately.

560
00:32:38.600 --> 00:32:39.680
I don't know. I…

561
00:32:41.000 --> 00:32:42.880
I thought I was a good boyfriend.

562
00:32:43.680 --> 00:32:45.120
Turns out I can't even do that.

563
00:32:45.640 --> 00:32:47.960
-[Sarah] Hey. Hey. come on.
-[faucet running]

564
00:32:51.280 --> 00:32:52.280
[door unlocking]

565
00:32:53.880 --> 00:32:56.000
-[Charlie] Hi.
-Hi.

566
00:32:56.800 --> 00:32:57.920
[Henry whining]

567
00:32:58.000 --> 00:32:58.920
-Hi.
-[Nick] Say hi.

568
00:32:59.000 --> 00:33:00.000
[Charlie] Hiya.

569
00:33:01.120 --> 00:33:02.360
Hello. Nellie.

570
00:33:03.600 --> 00:33:04.600
Does it hurt?

571
00:33:05.720 --> 00:33:06.840
Yeah. it hurts a bit.

572
00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:08.480
It's not too bad.

573
00:33:10.160 --> 00:33:11.600
Doing anything today?

574
00:33:13.680 --> 00:33:15.160
Not really. Um…

575
00:33:16.280 --> 00:33:17.480
Do you wanna come in?

576
00:33:18.320 --> 00:33:19.800
Do you wanna come round mine?

577
00:33:19.880 --> 00:33:22.400
My family are out.
and I've got a surprise for you.

578
00:33:23.240 --> 00:33:25.640
-[Nick chuckles softly]
-[Nellie whines. pants]

579
00:33:25.720 --> 00:33:26.760
[Charlie chuckles]

580
00:33:27.640 --> 00:33:30.720
♪ I spent a while ♪

581
00:33:31.760 --> 00:33:36.320
♪ Looking up at the moon ♪

582
00:33:37.000 --> 00:33:41.120
♪ I'll try to light ♪

583
00:33:41.640 --> 00:33:46.080
♪ All the candles above me ♪

584
00:33:47.120 --> 00:33:51.080
-♪ Don't wanna hide anymore ♪
-[Charlie chuckles]

585
00:33:51.160 --> 00:33:55.080
♪ From the light of the truth… ♪

586
00:33:55.600 --> 00:33:56.960
-[Nellie barks]
-[Nick] Oh!

587
00:33:57.040 --> 00:33:59.240
-Ha-ha!
-♪ And it's not your fault ♪

588
00:34:01.560 --> 00:34:05.720
♪ She looks like I do… ♪

589
00:34:05.800 --> 00:34:06.800
[Nick gasps]

590
00:34:07.320 --> 00:34:08.800
-Oi.
-[Charlie laughing]

591
00:34:08.880 --> 00:34:11.840
-[Nick] Wait. Okay. Okay!
-No! No. no. no. Don't!

592
00:34:11.920 --> 00:34:13.200
-[Charlie] Oh!
-[chuckles]

593
00:34:13.280 --> 00:34:15.720
-[Charlie] I'm gonna get you…
-No. no. no! Ah!

594
00:34:16.320 --> 00:34:18.280
-I'll get you back.
-No. no. no! Oh-oh!

595
00:34:18.400 --> 00:34:19.400
[Nick] Oh. yes!

596
00:34:19.880 --> 00:34:21.520
-No! Ah!
-[Nick] Okay.

597
00:34:21.600 --> 00:34:23.960
[Charlie] Hey. Nick. Nick. no!

598
00:34:24.040 --> 00:34:26.240
[both grunting playfully]

599
00:34:26.320 --> 00:34:28.040
[both giggling]

600
00:34:28.120 --> 00:34:31.440
-[chuckling] No. Wait. wait. Stop. stop.
-[Charlie giggling]

601
00:34:31.520 --> 00:34:32.960
-Ow!
-[Nick] Stop!

602
00:34:33.040 --> 00:34:35.480
[both laughing]

603
00:34:35.560 --> 00:34:36.720
[Nick] Oh.

604
00:34:36.800 --> 00:34:38.040
Oh wow.

605
00:34:38.120 --> 00:34:39.760
Oh. Whoo. Ah.

606
00:34:41.120 --> 00:34:43.800
The idea was a get-well-soon gift.

607
00:34:43.880 --> 00:34:46.640
but we could sit in there all day
while you're feeling rough.

608
00:34:46.720 --> 00:34:48.720
I got carried away with the construction.

609
00:34:49.520 --> 00:34:51.520
-[Nick] This is adorable.
-[both chuckle]

610
00:34:51.600 --> 00:34:52.720
Go on. then.

611
00:34:55.400 --> 00:34:56.480
[door closes]

612
00:34:56.560 --> 00:34:58.200
[gentle music playing]

613
00:35:03.680 --> 00:35:05.840
-Come on.
-[Charlie] I'm coming. I'm coming.

614
00:35:06.840 --> 00:35:07.840
[Nick chuckles]

615
00:35:09.720 --> 00:35:11.920
I got you something.
Early Christmas present.

616
00:35:12.000 --> 00:35:13.000
What?

617
00:35:14.760 --> 00:35:16.120
It's your last year of school.

618
00:35:16.200 --> 00:35:19.000
I thought you could record some memories.

619
00:35:19.080 --> 00:35:22.440
and then you can take them to Leeds
and put them on your wall or something.

620
00:35:23.320 --> 00:35:24.680
Let's give it a go.

621
00:35:27.560 --> 00:35:29.840
-[Charlie chuckles]
-Actually. wait. one more.

622
00:35:29.920 --> 00:35:32.480
Down here. Okay. Okay.

623
00:35:33.320 --> 00:35:34.240
-Ready?
-Yeah.

624
00:35:34.320 --> 00:35:35.320
Smile.

625
00:35:36.560 --> 00:35:38.080
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles softly]

626
00:35:39.120 --> 00:35:40.160
Thank you.

627
00:35:41.320 --> 00:35:45.040
-Probably could've waited until Christmas.
-Mm. I thought you needed cheering up.

628
00:35:45.560 --> 00:35:48.920
[Nick. softly] Mm. [sighs]

629
00:35:52.440 --> 00:35:54.640
Do you remember the first time we had sex?

630
00:35:54.720 --> 00:35:56.880
I remember that
in extremely graphic detail.

631
00:35:56.960 --> 00:35:59.760
[chuckles] Do you remember
what you said to me

632
00:36:00.800 --> 00:36:02.000
just before?

633
00:36:05.160 --> 00:36:06.160
You said that.

634
00:36:06.800 --> 00:36:08.680
I'm the only one you can talk to.

635
00:36:11.280 --> 00:36:12.680
That you felt lost.

636
00:36:15.360 --> 00:36:19.120
You know a couple of weeks back
when I had that dream about you dying?

637
00:36:20.200 --> 00:36:21.200
Yeah.

638
00:36:24.200 --> 00:36:28.640
It wasn't just you dying.
It was how you died.

639
00:36:30.200 --> 00:36:31.440
It was my fault.

640
00:36:32.520 --> 00:36:35.160
-Did you murder me in cold blood?
-No. I…

641
00:36:35.240 --> 00:36:36.920
[uneasy music playing]

642
00:36:37.000 --> 00:36:38.360
I missed the signs.

643
00:36:39.440 --> 00:36:42.400
It all happened again.
the stuff from last year. but…

644
00:36:43.680 --> 00:36:46.560
You didn't get help.
and you didn't get better. and…

645
00:36:49.080 --> 00:36:50.480
And when you were gone…

646
00:36:52.240 --> 00:36:53.680
Everything went blurry.

647
00:36:53.760 --> 00:36:57.360
You know. it was…
it was just me on my own in a house.

648
00:36:57.440 --> 00:36:59.880
and… there was nothing.

649
00:37:02.120 --> 00:37:03.440
I was nothing.

650
00:37:06.680 --> 00:37:09.040
It wasn't your fault
when I relapsed in January.

651
00:37:09.120 --> 00:37:10.640
-[Nick] It was.
-No. it wasn't.

652
00:37:10.720 --> 00:37:13.680
If I can't protect you. who even am I?

653
00:37:14.200 --> 00:37:16.040
If you don't need me anymore…

654
00:37:18.440 --> 00:37:19.840
I do need you.

655
00:37:21.880 --> 00:37:24.680
I need you because you're you.

656
00:37:26.000 --> 00:37:27.120
And I love you.

657
00:37:28.280 --> 00:37:30.920
-See. now I feel like a dick.
-[Charlie] Why?

658
00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:32.560
'Cause you shared a feeling?

659
00:37:32.640 --> 00:37:33.640
[Nick chuckles]

660
00:37:37.000 --> 00:37:38.000
Do you need me?

661
00:37:40.120 --> 00:37:41.120
Yeah.

662
00:37:42.920 --> 00:37:44.120
Yeah. So much.

663
00:37:46.240 --> 00:37:48.520
[romantic music playing]

664
00:37:55.120 --> 00:37:56.400
Can we have sex?

665
00:37:56.480 --> 00:37:57.760
[Charlie chuckles softly]

666
00:38:12.280 --> 00:38:14.200
[Nick breathing heavily]

667
00:38:23.160 --> 00:38:25.120
[Nick gasping]

668
00:38:28.960 --> 00:38:32.280
And I know this is the third time
we've "broken up."

669
00:38:32.360 --> 00:38:35.320
but I'm only using quotation marks
because is it really a break-up

670
00:38:35.400 --> 00:38:37.760
if we haven't literally said.
"Let's break up"?

671
00:38:38.280 --> 00:38:40.320
We're just temporarily not speaking.

672
00:38:40.840 --> 00:38:44.520
And we both know we'll get over it
in a couple of weeks. so I'm not worried.

673
00:38:45.440 --> 00:38:47.560
[sighs heavily] I'm not worried!

674
00:38:47.640 --> 00:38:49.600
-I believe you.
-You're looking at each other.

675
00:38:49.680 --> 00:38:52.640
-I can sense...
-No. you don't sound worried at all.

676
00:38:52.720 --> 00:38:54.760
[boys jeering]

677
00:38:54.840 --> 00:38:57.320
[Charlie] Oi!
What do you think you're doing?

678
00:38:57.400 --> 00:39:00.440
-[boy 1] We were just mucking around.
-Yeah. it's just banter.

679
00:39:00.520 --> 00:39:03.000
It didn't look like banter.
It looked like bullying.

680
00:39:04.240 --> 00:39:05.440
Leave.

681
00:39:05.520 --> 00:39:08.520
If I see you picking on anyone else again.
I'll get you suspended.

682
00:39:08.600 --> 00:39:10.840
-You can't suspend us.
-[Charlie] Try me.

683
00:39:15.200 --> 00:39:16.200
[boy 2 scoffs]

684
00:39:19.360 --> 00:39:20.560
You okay?

685
00:39:22.160 --> 00:39:24.800
Yeah. Yeah. I'm fine.

686
00:39:25.760 --> 00:39:28.160
Those boys aren't gonna
pick on you again. okay?

687
00:39:30.360 --> 00:39:32.160
[sighs] They might.

688
00:39:32.760 --> 00:39:35.680
-[Charlie] What's your name?
-Alfie.

689
00:39:35.760 --> 00:39:37.320
Hi. Alfie. I'm Charlie.

690
00:39:37.400 --> 00:39:38.880
I know.

691
00:39:40.680 --> 00:39:43.760
If they pick on you again.
come talk to me. I'll sort them out. Okay?

692
00:39:45.320 --> 00:39:46.520
Okay.

693
00:39:48.080 --> 00:39:49.840
[pensive music playing]

694
00:39:58.560 --> 00:40:01.680
I know I can't. like.
cure the world of homophobia.

695
00:40:01.760 --> 00:40:04.400
but there's probably so many kids
in the younger years

696
00:40:04.480 --> 00:40:06.600
who just think they're completely alone.

697
00:40:07.120 --> 00:40:09.360
If they had somewhere
to talk to people like them.

698
00:40:09.440 --> 00:40:11.480
maybe they wouldn't grow up
hating themselves.

699
00:40:11.560 --> 00:40:14.000
Well. you're more than welcome
to use my classroom.

700
00:40:14.080 --> 00:40:16.760
It doesn't even matter.
Mr. Lange already said no.

701
00:40:19.240 --> 00:40:22.360
I remember the first time
you appeared in my classroom.

702
00:40:22.440 --> 00:40:23.640
You were so quiet.

703
00:40:23.720 --> 00:40:27.600
and. you know. I'm really not supposed
to let people have their lunch in here.

704
00:40:27.680 --> 00:40:31.200
I've been lectured about it
by the deputy head many times.

705
00:40:31.720 --> 00:40:35.680
and every time I got told off.
I thought about you and your lunchbox

706
00:40:36.280 --> 00:40:38.040
and your sad little face.

707
00:40:38.560 --> 00:40:39.800
and I thought. "Well.

708
00:40:41.000 --> 00:40:43.960
he needs this. and I can help."

709
00:40:45.440 --> 00:40:46.600
And now look at you.

710
00:40:46.680 --> 00:40:50.160
-[chuckles softly]
-[Mr. Ajayi] I'm very proud of you.

711
00:40:52.000 --> 00:40:55.920
As your teacher. I'd say
you should respect Mr. Lange's decision.

712
00:40:56.000 --> 00:40:57.320
But.

713
00:40:57.840 --> 00:41:00.040
as a fellow homosexual.

714
00:41:00.120 --> 00:41:05.160
I'd say. historically. us queers
have never asked for permission to exist.

715
00:41:05.240 --> 00:41:08.200
-[intriguing music plays]
-[Mr. Ajayi] Do with that what you will.

716
00:41:14.320 --> 00:41:15.680
[Nick] Uh… Hello.

717
00:41:16.280 --> 00:41:19.120
I'm just here for the…
the part-time position.

718
00:41:19.200 --> 00:41:20.240
[man] Oh.

719
00:41:21.160 --> 00:41:22.320
You like animals?

720
00:41:22.400 --> 00:41:25.840
Yeah. Yeah. I. I. I have two dogs. so…

721
00:41:25.920 --> 00:41:29.760
And you wanna spend time with more dogs
because… what?

722
00:41:29.840 --> 00:41:33.560
I thought it might…
help me build character. [chuckles softly]

723
00:41:34.880 --> 00:41:36.960
I don't really do much outside of school.

724
00:41:37.040 --> 00:41:40.000
Um. I'm going to uni this year. so…

725
00:41:41.800 --> 00:41:45.000
-My partner told me to try something new.
-[man] Oh. did she?

726
00:41:45.080 --> 00:41:48.320
Well. aren't you Mr. Self-Improvement.

727
00:41:49.160 --> 00:41:50.880
I guess I have to hire you.

728
00:41:52.080 --> 00:41:53.800
Fill that in for me. please.

729
00:41:53.880 --> 00:41:55.680
[indie music playing]

730
00:41:56.800 --> 00:42:00.560
♪ You left your heart in the jungle… ♪

731
00:42:00.640 --> 00:42:01.640
Just joking.

732
00:42:01.720 --> 00:42:05.440
♪ Ripped off of your red bicycle ♪

733
00:42:05.520 --> 00:42:08.160
♪ I didn't know you then… ♪

734
00:42:09.280 --> 00:42:10.680
[Nick] There you go. buddy.

735
00:42:11.320 --> 00:42:12.360
[chuckling]

736
00:42:14.120 --> 00:42:18.480
♪ I gave up everything I learned ♪

737
00:42:18.560 --> 00:42:21.480
♪ Just to follow you down… ♪

738
00:42:21.560 --> 00:42:22.600
Biscuit.

739
00:42:22.680 --> 00:42:23.880
[Biscuit snorts softly]

740
00:42:27.280 --> 00:42:31.000
♪ There is no map for this ♪

741
00:42:31.640 --> 00:42:35.600
♪ When the wheels come off
I'll be your spare ♪

742
00:42:35.680 --> 00:42:41.120
♪ When the world turns on you
I will be there… ♪

743
00:42:41.200 --> 00:42:44.240
You know. you don't have to pick me up
after every shift.

744
00:42:44.320 --> 00:42:46.240
[chuckling] I like picking you up.

745
00:42:46.320 --> 00:42:49.320
-Plus. I wanna see the email in person.
-All right.

746
00:42:50.200 --> 00:42:51.680
-There you go.
-[Charlie] You did it!

747
00:42:51.760 --> 00:42:54.160
-[Nick] Mm-hmm.
-I'm so proud of you.

748
00:42:54.240 --> 00:42:57.080
[both grunting. groaning happily]

749
00:42:57.680 --> 00:43:00.376
[Charlie] I think if I post about it
on one of the Truham meme pages.

750
00:43:00.400 --> 00:43:02.720
lots of people will see it.
but Mr. Lange definitely won't.

751
00:43:02.800 --> 00:43:05.840
But I need to do it in a way
that won't attract bigoted comments.

752
00:43:05.920 --> 00:43:08.960
Who's even running the meme page
at the moment? Christian and Otis?

753
00:43:09.040 --> 00:43:12.080
-Uh. yeah. Yeah. I think so.
-[Charlie] I'll text them.

754
00:43:12.600 --> 00:43:13.760
Right. I'm heading out.

755
00:43:14.840 --> 00:43:17.720
Wait. I need more. It's our anniversary.

756
00:43:17.800 --> 00:43:18.920
[Nick] Hmm.

757
00:43:22.560 --> 00:43:24.680
Is that really
a two-year-anniversary kiss?

758
00:43:26.240 --> 00:43:29.360
-Mwah. mwah. mwah. mwah!
-[Charlie chuckling]

759
00:43:29.440 --> 00:43:32.840
-How was that. darling?
-Not enough. but it'll do till tonight.

760
00:43:32.920 --> 00:43:36.200
-[Nick] Something to look forward to.
-Meet me in the park at six?

761
00:43:36.280 --> 00:43:37.520
I will be there.

762
00:43:39.400 --> 00:43:40.440
Nick.

763
00:43:42.120 --> 00:43:43.120
I love you.

764
00:43:44.160 --> 00:43:45.160
I love you.

765
00:43:45.240 --> 00:43:47.240
[gentle music playing]

766
00:43:50.400 --> 00:43:51.400
[door closes]

767
00:44:06.520 --> 00:44:07.680
[cell phone dings. buzzes]

768
00:44:13.560 --> 00:44:14.720
[music fades]

769
00:44:15.320 --> 00:44:16.320
[Charlie sighs]

770
00:44:19.080 --> 00:44:20.720
-[sighs]
-[cell phone buzzes]

771
00:44:29.120 --> 00:44:30.200
[cell phone beeps]

772
00:44:31.200 --> 00:44:32.520
[barking in distance]

773
00:44:35.640 --> 00:44:36.640
[door opens]

774
00:44:40.000 --> 00:44:41.640
[man] How'd you meet her. then?

775
00:44:42.600 --> 00:44:43.480
Who?

776
00:44:43.560 --> 00:44:47.360
Only the girlfriend
you talk about nonstop every shift.

777
00:44:48.360 --> 00:44:49.640
We met in school.

778
00:44:51.920 --> 00:44:53.080
What's she like?

779
00:44:54.760 --> 00:44:55.880
He's. uh…

780
00:44:57.240 --> 00:44:58.800
He's a guy. actually.

781
00:45:00.680 --> 00:45:02.360
Oh. Right.

782
00:45:02.880 --> 00:45:04.040
Hmm. Pardon me.

783
00:45:04.120 --> 00:45:06.480
I… I'm not of the woke generation.

784
00:45:07.000 --> 00:45:09.880
I wouldn't have assumed.
You know. you don't seem gay at all.

785
00:45:11.240 --> 00:45:12.240
I'm bi.

786
00:45:14.360 --> 00:45:16.960
Oh. Well. yeah. Sure.

787
00:45:17.560 --> 00:45:18.560
Mm.

788
00:45:19.280 --> 00:45:21.400
Well. what's he like?

789
00:45:23.480 --> 00:45:24.480
He's…

790
00:45:27.040 --> 00:45:28.200
He's amazing.

791
00:45:30.040 --> 00:45:31.240
Very strong.

792
00:45:33.880 --> 00:45:36.520
[clears throat] Probably too good
for me. actually.

793
00:45:36.600 --> 00:45:40.280
Probably. But you're good
at picking up dog shit. aren't ya?

794
00:45:41.920 --> 00:45:43.160
Great. Thanks. Kenneth.

795
00:45:43.240 --> 00:45:46.040
I'm just saying.
someone's gotta scoop up the dog shit.

796
00:45:46.120 --> 00:45:48.200
or the world descends into chaos.

797
00:45:48.800 --> 00:45:49.800
[chuckles]

798
00:45:52.000 --> 00:45:53.000
[door closes]

799
00:45:53.800 --> 00:45:54.840
[Nick] Charlie.

800
00:45:56.960 --> 00:45:58.440
I'm so sorry.

801
00:46:00.840 --> 00:46:02.800
I wasn't thinking. and. um…

802
00:46:03.640 --> 00:46:07.080
You know. I just… I got in my head
about letting everybody down. and I just...

803
00:46:07.160 --> 00:46:08.240
[Charlie] It's okay.

804
00:46:08.840 --> 00:46:11.480
It's just some snacks and a blanket.
It's not a huge deal.

805
00:46:11.560 --> 00:46:12.720
It is.

806
00:46:12.800 --> 00:46:16.960
It's fine. Nick. it's… Probably too old
for this cringy stuff now. anyway.

807
00:46:17.040 --> 00:46:18.880
No. No. we're not. This is…

808
00:46:19.600 --> 00:46:21.080
No. this is lovely.

809
00:46:22.520 --> 00:46:23.760
My job is shit.

810
00:46:24.280 --> 00:46:26.280
I know. I… I should probably just quit.

811
00:46:26.360 --> 00:46:28.600
No. it's been good for you.
hasn't it? It's…

812
00:46:31.360 --> 00:46:35.120
-I don't want you to…
-Charlie. you're freezing. Come on.

813
00:46:39.440 --> 00:46:42.880
When you're in Leeds. I don't want you
to spend your time worrying about me.

814
00:46:42.960 --> 00:46:45.920
-Don't think about that now.
-I want you to be okay without me.

815
00:46:46.440 --> 00:46:47.720
[Nick sighs]

816
00:46:49.040 --> 00:46:50.120
Have you eaten?

817
00:46:51.600 --> 00:46:52.600
No.

818
00:46:53.160 --> 00:46:54.960
[Nick] Should we go home and eat there?

819
00:46:56.440 --> 00:46:57.640
Yours or mine?

820
00:46:57.720 --> 00:46:59.280
[gentle music playing]

821
00:46:59.360 --> 00:47:00.560
I don't mind.

822
00:47:04.480 --> 00:47:05.680
[Nick exhales sharply]

823
00:47:05.760 --> 00:47:07.160
-You're so cold.
-[chuckles]

824
00:47:07.240 --> 00:47:09.080
[Nick rubbing Charlie's hands]

825
00:47:09.840 --> 00:47:11.160
Let's warm you up.

826
00:47:11.960 --> 00:47:14.040
-[Charlie chuckles softly]
-[chuckles]

827
00:47:18.560 --> 00:47:20.440
[sighs] No one's coming.

828
00:47:20.960 --> 00:47:23.160
Look. just… just give it a minute.

829
00:47:23.240 --> 00:47:24.360
[Charlie sighs]

830
00:47:27.760 --> 00:47:28.760
[knocking on door]

831
00:47:31.200 --> 00:47:32.120
[Tao sighs]

832
00:47:32.200 --> 00:47:33.920
Don't look so disappointed.

833
00:47:34.000 --> 00:47:35.960
-We were in the middle of...
-Lads. chill.

834
00:47:36.920 --> 00:47:38.600
I'm… I'm part of the team.

835
00:47:40.680 --> 00:47:43.920
So. the rumors
about you two dating are true?

836
00:47:44.000 --> 00:47:46.280
Yes. Yes. Tao. they are true.

837
00:47:46.360 --> 00:47:47.800
[hits table] Called it.

838
00:47:47.880 --> 00:47:49.976
[Charlie] You didn't.
We've been telling you for ages.

839
00:47:50.000 --> 00:47:51.600
-If I say I called it. I did.
-[knocking]

840
00:47:51.680 --> 00:47:52.760
That's not how it works.

841
00:47:54.680 --> 00:47:55.680
Hello.

842
00:47:56.880 --> 00:48:00.080
-Hey! Hey. Come in. Come in.
-[soft rock music playing]

843
00:48:00.160 --> 00:48:02.000
[Charlie] Everyone. this is Alfie.

844
00:48:02.080 --> 00:48:03.840
-Hey. Alfie.
-[Tao] Come sit down. Alfie.

845
00:48:03.920 --> 00:48:06.040
-Do you want a cupcake?
-[Alfie] Yes. please.

846
00:48:06.120 --> 00:48:08.280
-[Tao] I chose that one.
-[door opens]

847
00:48:08.360 --> 00:48:10.960
-[Tao] It's that one.
-[Nick] It's a fancy cupcake.

848
00:48:11.560 --> 00:48:13.240
-[Charlie] Hi.
-[Tao] Please. come sit.

849
00:48:13.320 --> 00:48:15.040
-[Nick] Hello.
-[Isaac] Hey. guys.

850
00:48:15.120 --> 00:48:16.520
-Come in.
-Good to see you.

851
00:48:17.120 --> 00:48:19.720
[Charlie] I really want this to be
a safe space for all of you.

852
00:48:19.800 --> 00:48:21.560
but really mostly just to have fun.

853
00:48:21.640 --> 00:48:24.480
We're gonna watch some queer TV shows.
some queer films.

854
00:48:24.560 --> 00:48:27.320
Next week. Mr. Ajayi is gonna be
talking about Keith Haring.

855
00:48:27.400 --> 00:48:31.080
I want us to raise awareness and money
for queer communities around the world.

856
00:48:31.160 --> 00:48:34.800
I know we're one small group of people.
but I believe we can make a difference.

857
00:48:34.880 --> 00:48:37.000
[cheering. whooping]

858
00:48:37.080 --> 00:48:38.240
[Isaac] Bravo!

859
00:48:38.880 --> 00:48:39.880
[boy] Yeah!

860
00:48:42.880 --> 00:48:46.200
This one is Tao's. and that one's Elle's?

861
00:48:46.280 --> 00:48:49.800
Speaking of.
I think they've broken up again.

862
00:48:49.880 --> 00:48:51.560
The vibe is seriously uncomfortable.

863
00:48:51.640 --> 00:48:53.440
[Elle] When did we all
become coffee addicts?

864
00:48:53.520 --> 00:48:55.720
[Charlie] I think they're both
just very strong-willed.

865
00:48:55.800 --> 00:48:57.320
Sometimes that causes clashes.

866
00:48:57.400 --> 00:48:59.880
And they're way past
the honeymoon phase as well. so…

867
00:48:59.960 --> 00:49:03.520
Boys. are we seriously avoiding
talking about the obvious?

868
00:49:04.040 --> 00:49:06.000
Most teen relationships don't last.

869
00:49:06.600 --> 00:49:08.800
Maybe they'll break up for good this time.

870
00:49:09.560 --> 00:49:11.720
So tell me about Hannah.

871
00:49:11.800 --> 00:49:15.920
She said that she really liked me.
but that the distance was too much.

872
00:49:16.000 --> 00:49:20.200
And I was like. "Mm… Okay. well.
you're only in Birmingham." So…

873
00:49:20.280 --> 00:49:23.840
I'm glad I didn't get into Oxford.
Me and Darce don't have this problem.

874
00:49:23.920 --> 00:49:27.280
It's not just the couples. It's all of us.
We're all gonna be in different places.

875
00:49:27.360 --> 00:49:29.640
But Pride. next month.
you're all coming. yes?

876
00:49:29.720 --> 00:49:30.560
-Yes!
-Obviously.

877
00:49:30.640 --> 00:49:31.640
-Good.
-I'll be there.

878
00:49:31.720 --> 00:49:34.440
[Darcy] It'll probably be the last time
we hang out as a group.

879
00:49:34.520 --> 00:49:36.640
And then we'll never speak
to each other again.

880
00:49:36.720 --> 00:49:38.440
-[Imogen] Oh…
-[Darcy] Mm.

881
00:49:38.520 --> 00:49:40.480
Oh. I'm joking. [chuckling] I'm joking.

882
00:49:41.080 --> 00:49:44.040
-Obviously. we're all gonna keep talking.
-[Imogen] That makes me sad.

883
00:49:44.120 --> 00:49:46.160
[Elle] In 30 years.
we're gonna be middle-aged.

884
00:49:46.240 --> 00:49:49.720
causing a scene at a drag brunch
while Isaac's sat in a corner reading.

885
00:49:49.800 --> 00:49:52.280
[chuckling] Hopefully. I will have written
my own book by then.

886
00:49:52.760 --> 00:49:54.120
-[Charlie] Mm.
-[Elle] Mm!

887
00:49:54.640 --> 00:49:59.000
Nick always thinks about the future.
It's like he's there in his mind already.

888
00:49:59.080 --> 00:50:01.560
trying to stop a mistake
that hasn't happened yet.

889
00:50:01.640 --> 00:50:03.120
[Sahar giggling]

890
00:50:03.200 --> 00:50:06.080
But… I don't know what the mistake is.

891
00:50:06.160 --> 00:50:08.240
[group chattering in background]

892
00:50:08.320 --> 00:50:10.440
I never used to think
about the future at all.

893
00:50:11.320 --> 00:50:13.400
It's because you were too busy surviving.

894
00:50:13.480 --> 00:50:15.360
[pensive music plays]

895
00:50:16.600 --> 00:50:21.080
-[all singing] ♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
-[Sarah laughing]

896
00:50:21.160 --> 00:50:25.880
♪ Happy birthday. dear Sarah ♪

897
00:50:25.960 --> 00:50:26.800
Precarious.

898
00:50:26.880 --> 00:50:29.840
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

899
00:50:29.920 --> 00:50:33.120
-Oh. that looks yummy!
-[chuckling. cheering]

900
00:50:33.960 --> 00:50:36.040
[Charlie] Oh my God. you were so cute.

901
00:50:36.120 --> 00:50:38.400
[Nick] "Were"? I'm not cute anymore?

902
00:50:38.480 --> 00:50:42.560
[Charlie] Yeah. not as cute as this.
I mean. I'd protect him with my life.

903
00:50:42.640 --> 00:50:43.640
[Nick chuckles]

904
00:50:44.520 --> 00:50:45.520
Yeah.

905
00:50:46.160 --> 00:50:49.640
Right. I should. um.
I should go and say hi to some people.

906
00:50:49.720 --> 00:50:52.120
-I'll go to the loo and come find you.
-Okay.

907
00:50:53.920 --> 00:50:54.920
Hey.

908
00:50:55.400 --> 00:50:56.560
Cheese.

909
00:50:57.120 --> 00:50:59.080
[indistinct chattering in background]

910
00:51:01.960 --> 00:51:05.440
-50 is the new 30. All uphill from here.
-[Sarah chuckles]

911
00:51:05.520 --> 00:51:09.480
[woman] It feels like you truly blossomed
after you got rid of that silly man.

912
00:51:09.560 --> 00:51:11.760
Well. I did what I could. as did he.

913
00:51:11.840 --> 00:51:14.120
No. you did everything.
and he's an arsehole.

914
00:51:16.520 --> 00:51:19.200
-Sorry. One sec.
-[Sarah] Uh…

915
00:51:19.880 --> 00:51:21.680
I thought Dad was your hero.

916
00:51:22.200 --> 00:51:23.080
[scoffs]

917
00:51:23.160 --> 00:51:26.720
Heroes and villains.
That's the way your brain works. isn't it?

918
00:51:27.240 --> 00:51:28.920
[uneasy music playing]

919
00:51:30.320 --> 00:51:33.240
[sighs. in French] You need
to be tougher. Nicholas.

920
00:51:33.920 --> 00:51:35.360
Do you understand? Tougher.

921
00:51:36.240 --> 00:51:40.240
[sighs. in English] I thought
you were practicing your French. Nicholas.

922
00:51:41.440 --> 00:51:43.520
[sighs] It's disappointing.

923
00:51:44.120 --> 00:51:46.840
We'd be able to talk more. wouldn't we?

924
00:51:48.040 --> 00:51:48.920
[Stéphane sighs]

925
00:51:49.000 --> 00:51:51.480
-[indistinct background chatter]
-[Sarah laughing]

926
00:52:03.680 --> 00:52:04.680
You okay?

927
00:52:06.360 --> 00:52:08.040
[Nick] Uh. yeah. [clears throat]

928
00:52:08.640 --> 00:52:09.720
[Charlie] You sure?

929
00:52:10.520 --> 00:52:11.920
Mm. I'm fine.

930
00:52:12.920 --> 00:52:13.920
Come on.

931
00:52:15.920 --> 00:52:18.560
Do you think Tao and Elle
will break up for good this time?

932
00:52:25.400 --> 00:52:27.120
It's possible. I guess.

933
00:52:28.000 --> 00:52:29.000
Happens.

934
00:52:30.240 --> 00:52:32.880
Everyone thinks
teenage relationships don't last.

935
00:52:34.120 --> 00:52:35.760
I guess they usually don't.

936
00:52:36.720 --> 00:52:39.280
Well. I guess I'm an optimist. then.

937
00:52:41.200 --> 00:52:44.880
♪ So I'm gonna keep you in love with me ♪

938
00:52:45.360 --> 00:52:46.800
♪ For a while ♪

939
00:52:48.480 --> 00:52:51.760
♪ I'm gonna keep you in love with me ♪

940
00:52:55.360 --> 00:52:59.080
♪ I'm gonna keep you in love with me ♪

941
00:52:59.160 --> 00:53:00.520
♪ For a while ♪

942
00:53:01.320 --> 00:53:04.120
[dance music pumping in distance]

943
00:53:08.720 --> 00:53:10.280
-You all right. mate?
-Hey.

944
00:53:10.360 --> 00:53:12.120
[indistinct chattering]

945
00:53:15.280 --> 00:53:17.440
[girl] Yeah. I mean. I'm really excited.

946
00:53:18.360 --> 00:53:20.920
[cheering]

947
00:53:21.000 --> 00:53:23.680
Welcome to my humble abode. boys. [laughs]

948
00:53:23.760 --> 00:53:26.720
Oi. go get hammered
before the exams start. yeah?

949
00:53:26.800 --> 00:53:29.080
You see those two?
They are proper romantic. man.

950
00:53:29.160 --> 00:53:30.720
-Charlie!
-[Charlie] Hey.

951
00:53:30.800 --> 00:53:32.360
-[boys] Charlie!
-[Charlie] Hey.

952
00:53:32.440 --> 00:53:34.080
Yeah. yeah. I'm good.

953
00:53:36.400 --> 00:53:38.400
-[boy 2] Yeah.
-[girl 2] I mean…

954
00:53:44.800 --> 00:53:46.680
[Tara] I just got really tired.

955
00:53:47.720 --> 00:53:50.840
-Oh. hey. Nick. Come and join us.
-Hey.

956
00:53:51.960 --> 00:53:53.360
-[groans]
-[Elle] How've you been?

957
00:53:53.440 --> 00:53:55.080
-Yeah. not too bad.
-Here. have some.

958
00:53:55.160 --> 00:53:58.560
Yeah. that's it.
That's it! Harder. harder!

959
00:53:59.080 --> 00:54:02.520
-Go. go. go. go. go!
-[all cheering]

960
00:54:02.600 --> 00:54:05.400
…about. um.
about going traveling next year.

961
00:54:06.000 --> 00:54:07.160
Like. it would be good.

962
00:54:07.240 --> 00:54:10.160
It would be expensive.
but I think it could work. maybe.

963
00:54:10.840 --> 00:54:13.240
What… what are you doing.
or are you gonna think about it?

964
00:54:14.720 --> 00:54:16.960
-Sorry. I wasn't listening.
-[Darcy chuckles]

965
00:54:17.040 --> 00:54:19.920
-Nick. next year. uni.
-[chuckles]

966
00:54:22.000 --> 00:54:26.880
I know I should be really happy for him.
but… I just feel really sad.

967
00:54:28.360 --> 00:54:32.440
There. there. You're Nick
and Charlie. You're gonna be okay.

968
00:54:34.640 --> 00:54:36.080
[Tara] We basically grow up

969
00:54:36.160 --> 00:54:39.680
being brainwashed into thinking
there's only one possible future.

970
00:54:39.760 --> 00:54:43.280
Going to uni.
finding a career. settling down.

971
00:54:43.360 --> 00:54:46.200
No-one teaches you
that there are so many other options.

972
00:54:46.280 --> 00:54:47.640
especially if you're queer.

973
00:54:47.720 --> 00:54:51.560
That's why I asked Darcy
to go Interrailing with me next year.

974
00:54:51.640 --> 00:54:54.800
Just focus on being human
and feeling alive.

975
00:54:54.880 --> 00:54:57.960
I want that feeling.
It's just. me and Tao…

976
00:54:59.080 --> 00:55:02.960
People in good relationships don't keep
breaking up and getting back together.

977
00:55:03.040 --> 00:55:04.960
Well. you clearly don't wanna break up.

978
00:55:05.040 --> 00:55:07.360
I can't revolve my life
around someone else.

979
00:55:07.440 --> 00:55:09.880
It would only make us
resent each other eventually.

980
00:55:09.960 --> 00:55:12.000
and then it would kill
the love that's there.

981
00:55:12.640 --> 00:55:13.640
[Tara] True.

982
00:55:14.840 --> 00:55:17.720
-[electronic music playing]
-[boys chanting playfully]

983
00:55:21.600 --> 00:55:24.320
-[Sahar] Lights are getting on my nerves.
-I'm gonna find Nick.

984
00:55:24.400 --> 00:55:26.320
-[Sahar] Want us to come?
-No. it's all right.

985
00:55:27.240 --> 00:55:29.120
[Tao] I haven't seen Nick in a while.

986
00:55:29.880 --> 00:55:34.560
-[boy laughing]
-[boys chanting playfully]

987
00:55:35.200 --> 00:55:37.960
[electronic music continues]

988
00:55:43.760 --> 00:55:46.640
-[boy retching]
-[boys] Urgh! [laughing]

989
00:55:57.040 --> 00:55:59.280
-[Elle] Yeah.
-[Isaac] Shall we go outside for a bit?

990
00:55:59.360 --> 00:56:01.760
-[Charlie] I think he might be upstairs.
-Okay.

991
00:56:02.280 --> 00:56:04.480
[music thumping in distance]

992
00:56:12.640 --> 00:56:13.800
Hey.

993
00:56:14.440 --> 00:56:15.600
Did you wanna go?

994
00:56:16.280 --> 00:56:18.840
[exhales sharply] Yeah. Yeah. I guess.

995
00:56:18.920 --> 00:56:20.680
O… only if you want to.

996
00:56:22.160 --> 00:56:25.160
-It is a bit boring. isn't it? So…
-[chuckles] Yeah.

997
00:56:28.200 --> 00:56:29.240
Hey. Um…

998
00:56:31.800 --> 00:56:33.680
Are you angry at me about something?

999
00:56:33.760 --> 00:56:35.960
What? N… no.

1000
00:56:37.120 --> 00:56:38.440
Why do you think that?

1001
00:56:38.520 --> 00:56:41.240
You've avoided me tonight.

1002
00:56:41.320 --> 00:56:42.720
I'm sorry. I…

1003
00:56:44.640 --> 00:56:47.040
I just wanted you
to have a good night. and…

1004
00:56:48.240 --> 00:56:51.880
You know. you. you probably wanna
talk to your friends about uni.

1005
00:56:52.800 --> 00:56:55.240
It's only. like. four months away now. so…

1006
00:56:57.080 --> 00:56:58.240
Sure. Um…

1007
00:57:00.040 --> 00:57:01.880
It's gonna be really hard
when you're not here.

1008
00:57:02.400 --> 00:57:04.920
[scoffs] No. you're…
you're gonna be great.

1009
00:57:05.000 --> 00:57:09.280
-You don't need me hanging around.
-It's still gonna be really hard.

1010
00:57:11.200 --> 00:57:13.520
What if everything just blows up.
like Tao and Elle?

1011
00:57:14.240 --> 00:57:16.800
[hesitates] I mean.
I guess that's possible.

1012
00:57:19.560 --> 00:57:21.560
I know you've been struggling this year.

1013
00:57:22.800 --> 00:57:26.040
You've been really anxious
about a lot of things. about yourself.

1014
00:57:26.120 --> 00:57:28.960
Yeah. sorry. I know
that's probably annoying for you.

1015
00:57:29.840 --> 00:57:33.360
It's not annoying. It's just… upsetting.

1016
00:57:34.000 --> 00:57:38.160
'Cause… [sighs] …I try and talk to you
about it. and you just shut down.

1017
00:57:39.000 --> 00:57:40.880
And I thought we were good at that.

1018
00:57:43.080 --> 00:57:46.080
And I think that the reason you do that
is… is because of me.

1019
00:57:49.120 --> 00:57:52.080
Maybe it is a good idea
for us to have some space. you know?

1020
00:57:53.240 --> 00:57:56.360
You're going off to uni.
and you'll be living your best life.

1021
00:57:56.440 --> 00:57:59.840
and then maybe if you don't
have to worry about me so much. then…

1022
00:57:59.920 --> 00:58:01.160
Then you'll be happier.

1023
00:58:02.720 --> 00:58:04.200
I want you to be happy.

1024
00:58:04.720 --> 00:58:06.600
So we should break up. then?

1025
00:58:07.120 --> 00:58:08.640
[Nick sighs]

1026
00:58:09.160 --> 00:58:10.760
For some space? That's…

1027
00:58:10.840 --> 00:58:13.720
[sighs] That's basically
what you're saying. isn't it?

1028
00:58:17.480 --> 00:58:20.560
-If… if that's what you want.
-No. I'm asking if that's what you want.

1029
00:58:20.640 --> 00:58:23.480
-I want you to be happy.
-I'm only happy when I'm with you.

1030
00:58:23.560 --> 00:58:25.560
I don't think that's how it should be.

1031
00:58:29.320 --> 00:58:31.160
-[sniffles] I get it.
-What?

1032
00:58:31.240 --> 00:58:33.680
-No. it's fine.
-I don't want to break up.

1033
00:58:33.760 --> 00:58:35.680
I think you'd be better off
without me too.

1034
00:58:35.760 --> 00:58:38.120
I didn't say that. Nick. I…

1035
00:58:38.640 --> 00:58:41.320
-[Nick] I'm sorry.
-I… I'm just trying to help.

1036
00:58:41.400 --> 00:58:42.920
-[Nick] It's okay.
-I love you.

1037
00:58:43.000 --> 00:58:44.000
[Nick] It's okay.

1038
00:58:45.280 --> 00:58:46.960
You don't have to worry about me.

1039
00:58:56.360 --> 00:58:58.200
I'm sorry for making you cry.

1040
00:59:03.080 --> 00:59:04.680
[door opens]

1041
00:59:07.520 --> 00:59:08.760
[Charlie sighs]

1042
00:59:09.440 --> 00:59:10.280
[sighs]

1043
00:59:10.360 --> 00:59:12.360
[electronic music playing in distance]

1044
00:59:14.560 --> 00:59:15.680
[car door unlocks]

1045
00:59:18.720 --> 00:59:21.120
[breathing heavily]

1046
00:59:22.480 --> 00:59:23.840
[sighs]

1047
00:59:23.920 --> 00:59:27.400
-[uneasy music playing]
-[Nick breathing shakily]

1048
00:59:32.600 --> 00:59:34.440
[music turns darker]

1049
00:59:35.920 --> 00:59:37.760
[pensive music playing]

1050
00:59:37.840 --> 00:59:38.960
[sighs]

1051
00:59:45.200 --> 00:59:46.880
[both chuckling]

1052
00:59:52.720 --> 00:59:54.160
[sighs. sniffles]

1053
01:00:05.880 --> 01:00:07.000
[exhales shakily]

1054
01:00:10.840 --> 01:00:12.560
[music fades]

1055
01:00:27.360 --> 01:00:29.960
[uneasy music playing]

1056
01:00:33.680 --> 01:00:38.240
I know this is difficult.
but. Charlie. you've got to eat.

1057
01:00:38.760 --> 01:00:39.760
Please.

1058
01:00:41.560 --> 01:00:43.160
[Julio] Come on. hmm?

1059
01:00:45.280 --> 01:00:46.680
Just a little bite.

1060
01:00:50.320 --> 01:00:52.680
Charlie. we're gonna do
a refocusing exercise.

1061
01:00:53.200 --> 01:00:56.200
I want you to tell me five things
that you see in front of you.

1062
01:00:59.640 --> 01:01:00.640
[flatly] Door.

1063
01:01:01.600 --> 01:01:02.800
Desk.

1064
01:01:05.200 --> 01:01:06.320
Laptop.

1065
01:01:09.120 --> 01:01:10.120
Mug.

1066
01:01:12.720 --> 01:01:13.760
Photo.

1067
01:01:18.960 --> 01:01:20.440
[tapping keyboard]

1068
01:01:24.640 --> 01:01:25.720
[sighs]

1069
01:01:34.280 --> 01:01:35.720
[sighs]

1070
01:01:53.480 --> 01:01:55.320
[sighs heavily]

1071
01:02:01.000 --> 01:02:02.840
[rhythmic knocking on door]

1072
01:02:05.080 --> 01:02:06.120
[rapid knocking]

1073
01:02:07.160 --> 01:02:08.760
[persistent. loud knocking]

1074
01:02:08.840 --> 01:02:10.200
Go away!

1075
01:02:10.280 --> 01:02:11.280
[Tao] Charlie!

1076
01:02:11.360 --> 01:02:13.240
-[sighs]
-[Tao] We're coming in. okay?

1077
01:02:16.160 --> 01:02:17.080
What?

1078
01:02:17.160 --> 01:02:19.760
You can't just lie there
and expect everything to be okay.

1079
01:02:19.840 --> 01:02:22.840
[Isaac] Let's just take a minute. okay.
before you say something crazy.

1080
01:02:22.920 --> 01:02:24.320
[exhales deeply]

1081
01:02:24.400 --> 01:02:26.080
We're here to look after you.

1082
01:02:26.160 --> 01:02:27.640
Getting you out of the house.

1083
01:02:27.720 --> 01:02:30.720
or just hanging out here
and bringing you food and comfort movies.

1084
01:02:30.800 --> 01:02:32.320
Tori said you hadn't been eating.

1085
01:02:32.400 --> 01:02:34.360
Which is understandable.
We don't blame you.

1086
01:02:34.440 --> 01:02:38.080
But it's not great.
so we're gonna make you some pasta.

1087
01:02:38.760 --> 01:02:40.360
Aren't you two broken up right now?

1088
01:02:42.480 --> 01:02:44.560
We've organized a temporary truce.

1089
01:02:44.640 --> 01:02:48.040
and anyway. three. two…

1090
01:02:49.080 --> 01:02:50.120
-Go!
-Tao!

1091
01:02:50.200 --> 01:02:51.680
-Come on. Get up.
-[Charlie] Tao!

1092
01:02:51.760 --> 01:02:54.920
-[Tao] Get some pasta with some chili oil.
-Okay. I'm up. I'm up.

1093
01:02:55.000 --> 01:02:56.600
-[Tao] Cheese. Basil.
-I hate all of you.

1094
01:02:56.640 --> 01:02:57.640
[Elle] We love you too.

1095
01:02:57.680 --> 01:02:59.040
[sweeping music playing]

1096
01:02:59.120 --> 01:03:01.200
[Colette playing on TV]
But some bit of luck.

1097
01:03:01.280 --> 01:03:05.840
some commonplace little miracle.
which. like a glittering link.

1098
01:03:06.360 --> 01:03:09.840
will mend again the necklace of my days.

1099
01:03:16.400 --> 01:03:19.200
-[music ends with flourish]
-[snoring]

1100
01:03:25.160 --> 01:03:26.800
We'll see you on Saturday?

1101
01:03:27.800 --> 01:03:28.800
I don't know.

1102
01:03:28.840 --> 01:03:29.960
That wasn't a question.

1103
01:03:30.040 --> 01:03:32.120
It might do you good
to get out of the house.

1104
01:03:32.200 --> 01:03:34.880
But it's Pride. isn't it?
It's… it's a whole thing.

1105
01:03:34.960 --> 01:03:39.960
And I don't really feel like celebrating
the magical wonders of gay love right now.

1106
01:03:41.560 --> 01:03:42.880
And he might be there.

1107
01:03:45.760 --> 01:03:48.040
Charlie. I know you're hurting.

1108
01:03:48.120 --> 01:03:51.920
but I need you to come
and march with me on Saturday

1109
01:03:52.000 --> 01:03:53.880
because I'm fucking scared.

1110
01:03:54.840 --> 01:03:56.720
The world hates me right now.

1111
01:03:56.800 --> 01:04:00.520
The government is taking away my rights
and everything we fought for.

1112
01:04:00.600 --> 01:04:02.000
If I was a few years younger.

1113
01:04:02.080 --> 01:04:05.080
I wouldn't even have been able
to take hormone blockers legally

1114
01:04:05.600 --> 01:04:06.880
'cause they banned them.

1115
01:04:06.960 --> 01:04:09.320
People don't want me
using public bathrooms

1116
01:04:10.280 --> 01:04:11.720
or existing at all.

1117
01:04:15.080 --> 01:04:17.000
I just wanna be myself.

1118
01:04:18.760 --> 01:04:20.160
To be free.

1119
01:04:20.240 --> 01:04:22.000
[pensive music playing]

1120
01:04:22.080 --> 01:04:23.520
To be happy.

1121
01:04:24.320 --> 01:04:25.360
[breathes shakily]

1122
01:04:26.280 --> 01:04:27.560
I know you know all of this.

1123
01:04:27.640 --> 01:04:30.800
and it's okay if you come
and cry about Nick all day.

1124
01:04:31.320 --> 01:04:32.320
But…

1125
01:04:34.080 --> 01:04:35.760
I'm terrified all the time.

1126
01:04:36.280 --> 01:04:40.000
and I just really need my best friends
with me to march at Pride. okay?

1127
01:04:47.080 --> 01:04:48.480
[Elle] Mm.

1128
01:04:49.680 --> 01:04:51.400
[upbeat music playing]

1129
01:04:51.480 --> 01:04:53.800
[group chanting. cheering]

1130
01:04:59.960 --> 01:05:01.080
[woman] Woo-hoo!

1131
01:05:01.160 --> 01:05:02.680
Yeah!

1132
01:05:02.760 --> 01:05:05.600
[whooping. cheering. whistling]

1133
01:05:08.920 --> 01:05:09.760
Oh my God!

1134
01:05:09.840 --> 01:05:11.240
Whoo!

1135
01:05:11.760 --> 01:05:14.600
-Oh. it's James! Hello!
-[James] Hi. everyone.

1136
01:05:14.680 --> 01:05:16.480
-[Imogen] Oh. James!
-Happy Pride!

1137
01:05:16.560 --> 01:05:18.680
Happy Pride. Hi. are you okay?

1138
01:05:18.760 --> 01:05:21.160
-[Tao] Hey.
-[Isaac] Hi. Oh. you look amazing.

1139
01:05:21.240 --> 01:05:23.600
-[James] Nice to see you. See you later.
-[Isaac] Bye.

1140
