[door opens]

1239
01:11:35.440 --> 01:11:37.560
[video game music playing]

1240
01:11:40.040 --> 01:11:41.520
[David] Still sulking?

1241
01:11:46.640 --> 01:11:47.640
[door closes]

1242
01:11:49.320 --> 01:11:50.480
[David sighs]

1243
01:11:51.280 --> 01:11:53.960
I mean. it's… it's rough though.

1244
01:11:59.240 --> 01:12:00.720
[David sighs]

1245
01:12:00.800 --> 01:12:02.640
Genuinely. I feel for you.

1246
01:12:05.720 --> 01:12:07.040
You wanna talk. or…?

1247
01:12:08.840 --> 01:12:09.760
[Nick sighs]

1248
01:12:09.840 --> 01:12:11.320
[snickers] Okay…

1249
01:12:13.680 --> 01:12:15.240
Oh. I'm going to Paris.

1250
01:12:16.560 --> 01:12:18.000
Dad offered me a job.

1251
01:12:18.680 --> 01:12:21.680
So I'll be gone.
I'm sure that'll cheer you up.

1252
01:12:23.960 --> 01:12:24.960
[game pauses]

1253
01:12:25.360 --> 01:12:29.360
[chuckles] I know you think
I worship him. but I… I really…

1254
01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:32.000
I don't.

1255
01:12:32.520 --> 01:12:34.320
He's a shit dad.

1256
01:12:34.920 --> 01:12:36.360
Always has been. but…

1257
01:12:38.360 --> 01:12:40.040
I'm not like him. Nick.

1258
01:12:43.880 --> 01:12:45.440
You know. he hurt me too.

1259
01:12:48.600 --> 01:12:49.600
I know.

1260
01:12:57.960 --> 01:12:59.200
[cell phone chimes]

1261
01:12:59.280 --> 01:13:01.280
[gentle music plays]

1262
01:13:05.520 --> 01:13:06.720
[Nick sighs]

1263
01:13:09.360 --> 01:13:10.680
[cell phone buzzes]

1264
01:13:14.800 --> 01:13:17.120
[tapping keyboard]

1265
01:13:26.920 --> 01:13:28.000
[sighs]

1266
01:13:32.160 --> 01:13:33.920
[music fades]

1267
01:13:35.040 --> 01:13:38.720
-Ooh. there's mine. What you having?
-Do you think they have organic wine?

1268
01:13:38.800 --> 01:13:41.560
Organic wine?
Wine is wine. You need to just drink.

1269
01:13:41.640 --> 01:13:44.560
No. no. no. no. None of that now.
Organic wine. it's imp...

1270
01:13:44.640 --> 01:13:47.240
-[Sahar[ Nick! How you doing?
-Hello. Yeah. I'm all right.

1271
01:13:47.320 --> 01:13:50.520
-First time in a gay club?
-Uh. yeah. Yeah. I guess.

1272
01:13:50.600 --> 01:13:53.320
-[giggles] You'll get used to it.
-Mine too.

1273
01:13:55.840 --> 01:13:59.400
I… never got to tell you I'm a lesbian.

1274
01:14:01.840 --> 01:14:03.480
Guess we drifted apart a bit.

1275
01:14:06.480 --> 01:14:07.760
We have. yeah.

1276
01:14:10.040 --> 01:14:11.080
I'm sorry.

1277
01:14:16.200 --> 01:14:17.760
Do you remember

1278
01:14:17.840 --> 01:14:21.640
when we would sit outside the school gates
and pretend we were cool?

1279
01:14:21.720 --> 01:14:22.720
[Nick chuckles]

1280
01:14:23.400 --> 01:14:25.360
-Unfortunately. I do. yeah.
-[chuckles]

1281
01:14:26.800 --> 01:14:28.560
I just wanted everyone to like me.

1282
01:14:29.440 --> 01:14:31.720
That was all I cared about.

1283
01:14:33.720 --> 01:14:36.360
-Thank God we got out of there. you know?
-[Nick] Mm.

1284
01:14:36.440 --> 01:14:37.480
[Sahar] Cheers.

1285
01:14:38.160 --> 01:14:39.760
[cubicle door unlocking]

1286
01:14:39.840 --> 01:14:41.160
[zipper closing]

1287
01:14:44.520 --> 01:14:46.200
[faucet running]

1288
01:14:50.560 --> 01:14:51.720
[door opening]

1289
01:14:53.640 --> 01:14:54.640
Hi.

1290
01:14:55.200 --> 01:14:56.520
-[Nick] Hey.
-Wait.

1291
01:14:56.600 --> 01:14:59.520
Did you get my messages?
We've all been really worried about you.

1292
01:14:59.600 --> 01:15:01.040
-[man] Sorry. guys.
-[Tao] Sorry.

1293
01:15:01.120 --> 01:15:03.680
Charlie's not… Well. he's…

1294
01:15:03.760 --> 01:15:05.200
Is he okay?

1295
01:15:05.720 --> 01:15:08.520
Yeah. he's…
Can you just come and talk to him?

1296
01:15:09.680 --> 01:15:12.080
-What. he's here?
-Of course he's here.

1297
01:15:12.600 --> 01:15:15.320
This is insane. You get…
you get this is insane. don't you?

1298
01:15:15.400 --> 01:15:16.640
[sighs] Breakups are normal.

1299
01:15:16.720 --> 01:15:18.720
-Teenage romance...
-Are you being serious?

1300
01:15:19.320 --> 01:15:20.840
Have you seen yourselves?

1301
01:15:21.360 --> 01:15:25.640
You've guided each other through all
this emotional growth and pain together.

1302
01:15:25.720 --> 01:15:29.200
You can communicate just by looking
at each other. Trust me. I can see it.

1303
01:15:29.880 --> 01:15:32.280
I'm sorry. I can't.

1304
01:15:33.240 --> 01:15:34.240
Nick.

1305
01:15:36.280 --> 01:15:38.280
[electropop music playing]

1306
01:15:49.280 --> 01:15:53.080
Nicholas. Where have you been?
This is my friend Megan.

1307
01:15:53.160 --> 01:15:54.600
-[Megan] Hey.
-Hey.

1308
01:15:54.680 --> 01:15:56.480
Imogen was just telling me
about your breakup.

1309
01:15:56.560 --> 01:16:00.000
And. like. I'm so sorry.
That is. like. so sad.

1310
01:16:01.000 --> 01:16:02.560
It's all right. Thank you though.

1311
01:16:02.640 --> 01:16:06.000
Sorry. I. I know
it's. like. none of my business. um.

1312
01:16:06.680 --> 01:16:08.840
but if you wanted a quick rebound.

1313
01:16:08.920 --> 01:16:11.600
I have several mates
I could hook you up with.

1314
01:16:11.680 --> 01:16:14.560
Boys or… girls?

1315
01:16:16.080 --> 01:16:17.160
Uh…

1316
01:16:17.840 --> 01:16:20.520
-No pressure though. No pressure.
-Yeah. um…

1317
01:16:21.120 --> 01:16:23.360
I think I'm all right. actually.
Thank you though.

1318
01:16:23.440 --> 01:16:25.360
-[Megan] Okay. Bye.
-Nice to meet you.

1319
01:16:29.640 --> 01:16:35.240
♪ It's over now ♪

1320
01:16:37.200 --> 01:16:38.840
♪ Camera ♪

1321
01:16:39.880 --> 01:16:41.960
♪ Caught on camera ♪

1322
01:16:42.920 --> 01:16:45.400
♪ The girls on camera ♪

1323
01:16:46.280 --> 01:16:49.000
♪ Your girl's a fan of ♪

1324
01:16:50.000 --> 01:16:51.680
[music fades]

1325
01:16:53.960 --> 01:16:56.400
-Afternoon. lovey.
-Afternoon.

1326
01:16:56.480 --> 01:16:57.920
-Hello.
-Hi.

1327
01:16:58.000 --> 01:17:00.280
-Two black coffees. please.
-Of course.

1328
01:17:03.640 --> 01:17:04.640
[man 1 groans]

1329
01:17:06.640 --> 01:17:08.480
-You all right. Pooh?
-Yeah.

1330
01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:12.160
[man 2] Good to get out again. isn't it?
Stretch the legs.

1331
01:17:12.240 --> 01:17:15.240
[man 1] Oh yes. No. I couldn't give a...

1332
01:17:15.320 --> 01:17:16.640
Oh. stop it.

1333
01:17:16.720 --> 01:17:19.040
-[Charlie] Here you go.
-Thank you.

1334
01:17:19.120 --> 01:17:22.840
And there was a spare slice of cake.
so this one's on the house.

1335
01:17:22.920 --> 01:17:26.880
That's very sweet. but Pete's a diabetic.
We don't have cake at home.

1336
01:17:26.960 --> 01:17:27.880
Oh. sorry.

1337
01:17:27.960 --> 01:17:31.200
You eat it. Pooh. We're not both diabetic.

1338
01:17:31.280 --> 01:17:34.440
That's very kind of you. lovey. but…
Thank you.

1339
01:17:35.720 --> 01:17:38.520
-[Pete] Thank you.
-Now. let's do the crossword.

1340
01:17:38.600 --> 01:17:39.960
Oh yes. the crossword.

1341
01:17:40.040 --> 01:17:42.360
-If we must. [giggles]
-Oh! [chuckles]

1342
01:17:42.440 --> 01:17:44.880
-[Pete] Anything to shut me up.
-[both chuckle]

1343
01:17:45.520 --> 01:17:48.200
[Pete] Oh dear. I think I've got…

1344
01:17:48.280 --> 01:17:50.880
-[man 2] Oh. You like the crossword.
-[Pete] Well. yes.

1345
01:17:50.960 --> 01:17:53.160
-[man 2] You ninny.
-[Pete] There's a time and a place.

1346
01:17:53.240 --> 01:17:56.160
-[man 2] It's surprising…
-[both chattering indistinctly]

1347
01:17:56.240 --> 01:17:57.600
-[man 2] Now.
-[Pete groans]

1348
01:17:58.640 --> 01:18:00.480
[man 2] Anna is going to come
and stay with you

1349
01:18:00.520 --> 01:18:02.840
until they've finished with me
in the hospital.

1350
01:18:02.920 --> 01:18:06.000
It'll all be okay. Pooh.
I know you're worried about me.

1351
01:18:06.600 --> 01:18:09.840
It's the sort of thing
you do worry about. isn't it?

1352
01:18:09.920 --> 01:18:11.440
Yes. it is.

1353
01:18:12.480 --> 01:18:14.840
We look after each other. don't we?

1354
01:18:16.840 --> 01:18:18.600
I suppose so. [chuckles]

1355
01:18:19.200 --> 01:18:21.720
Two days with Anna. I mean…

1356
01:18:21.800 --> 01:18:23.320
[man 2] You usually complain…

1357
01:18:25.040 --> 01:18:26.920
[tapping keyboard]

1358
01:18:41.920 --> 01:18:42.800
[frustrated sigh]

1359
01:18:42.880 --> 01:18:44.400
[music fades]

1360
01:18:47.880 --> 01:18:48.880
[sighs]

1361
01:18:51.600 --> 01:18:55.280
♪ Don't go far
Don't go put your feet in… ♪

1362
01:18:55.880 --> 01:18:57.680
Hi. picking up for Charlie Spring.

1363
01:19:01.680 --> 01:19:03.560
-Do you want a bag?
-Yes. please.

1364
01:19:04.240 --> 01:19:05.240
Thank you.

1365
01:19:07.640 --> 01:19:08.760
Okay.

1366
01:19:09.520 --> 01:19:10.640
[Nick sighs]

1367
01:19:10.720 --> 01:19:14.680
I know it's scary when the other dogs
are here. but it's just you and me.

1368
01:19:15.200 --> 01:19:19.520
♪ Making up. lovers on their own tonight ♪

1369
01:19:19.600 --> 01:19:23.280
♪ Need to see how it's done
So I can change inside ♪

1370
01:19:23.360 --> 01:19:27.040
♪ I belong with everyone
Everyone I've ever known ♪

1371
01:19:27.120 --> 01:19:31.800
♪ I belong with everyone
Everyone I've ever known is here ♪

1372
01:19:34.920 --> 01:19:35.960
♪ With me ♪

1373
01:19:40.080 --> 01:19:43.000
♪ Everything that comes together… ♪

1374
01:19:43.080 --> 01:19:45.360
-[barks]
-Sit. Sit.

1375
01:19:45.440 --> 01:19:47.000
And run!

1376
01:19:47.560 --> 01:19:48.880
Oh. good boy.

1377
01:19:48.960 --> 01:19:52.640
♪ In every single living thing… ♪

1378
01:19:54.920 --> 01:19:56.480
Ready? Ready?

1379
01:19:58.200 --> 01:20:01.680
Run! Oh. I was just joking.
I was just joking.

1380
01:20:02.960 --> 01:20:05.200
Good boy. Good boy!

1381
01:20:05.280 --> 01:20:08.720
♪ In every single living thing… ♪

1382
01:20:08.800 --> 01:20:09.800
Hey.

1383
01:20:18.960 --> 01:20:20.160
-All right.
-Thank you.

1384
01:20:20.240 --> 01:20:21.520
You guys are good to go.

1385
01:20:22.280 --> 01:20:24.280
-Thank you so much.
-No worries.

1386
01:20:24.960 --> 01:20:26.640
-Call if there's any problems.
-Sure.

1387
01:20:26.720 --> 01:20:27.840
See you. Biscuit.

1388
01:20:27.920 --> 01:20:31.560
♪ Maybe if you've got someone
You should let them know ♪

1389
01:20:33.240 --> 01:20:34.240
[Biscuit whimpers]

1390
01:20:35.600 --> 01:20:38.000
-[chuckles softly]
-[music fades]

1391
01:20:38.080 --> 01:20:39.400
-[door closes]
-[Nick] Hello.

1392
01:20:39.480 --> 01:20:41.000
[Sarah] Someone's cheerful.

1393
01:20:42.880 --> 01:20:45.480
Yeah. you know that dog
that was struggling?

1394
01:20:45.560 --> 01:20:47.360
He just got adopted today. so…

1395
01:20:47.440 --> 01:20:51.280
[Sarah] Oh. I knew you'd be good
at this job. You're like a dog whisperer.

1396
01:20:53.320 --> 01:20:56.080
-Good to see you smiling again.
-Yeah.

1397
01:20:57.240 --> 01:20:59.480
Your brother's moving out.

1398
01:21:02.080 --> 01:21:03.600
Yeah. he told me that.

1399
01:21:05.520 --> 01:21:06.800
I think it's a mistake.

1400
01:21:06.880 --> 01:21:10.480
So do I. but you know what he's like.
He can't be told things.

1401
01:21:14.240 --> 01:21:16.280
[Nick sighs heavily]

1402
01:21:18.200 --> 01:21:20.480
God. Dad really fucked us up. didn't he?

1403
01:21:21.680 --> 01:21:23.320
Years after he left. I…

1404
01:21:23.400 --> 01:21:28.240
I was still just moving through life
with a fake smile on my face.

1405
01:21:30.120 --> 01:21:32.280
I couldn't even make real friends until…

1406
01:21:37.400 --> 01:21:39.080
It's still in my brain.

1407
01:21:42.640 --> 01:21:46.760
And now he's ruined the one
beautiful thing that I had in my life.

1408
01:21:46.840 --> 01:21:48.160
because I thought

1409
01:21:49.560 --> 01:21:54.000
if I even stepped a toe out of line.
if I was ever too sad or…

1410
01:21:54.920 --> 01:21:56.200
Or angry

1411
01:21:57.440 --> 01:21:59.680
or difficult. then he would just leave.

1412
01:22:02.000 --> 01:22:03.000
[sighs]

1413
01:22:05.440 --> 01:22:06.920
God. it's all wrong.

1414
01:22:08.520 --> 01:22:10.000
I didn't wanna break up.

1415
01:22:10.080 --> 01:22:11.960
[pensive music playing]

1416
01:22:12.720 --> 01:22:14.320
[Sarah] Well. that's a relief.

1417
01:22:16.240 --> 01:22:19.000
Do you know. sweetheart.
some people go a whole lifetime

1418
01:22:19.080 --> 01:22:22.720
without knowing themselves even a fraction
of what you've just expressed.

1419
01:22:23.480 --> 01:22:25.680
Look at me. I ended up marrying a man
who abandoned ship

1420
01:22:25.760 --> 01:22:27.920
as soon as our kids
weren't babies anymore.

1421
01:22:28.960 --> 01:22:31.280
-I see my part in the mistakes…
-No...

1422
01:22:31.360 --> 01:22:33.360
No. it's fine.
I don't blame myself anymore.

1423
01:22:33.440 --> 01:22:36.160
What I'm saying is.
I wish I'd known myself better.

1424
01:22:36.240 --> 01:22:39.640
I wish I'd understood him better.
understood our relationship better.

1425
01:22:41.080 --> 01:22:44.080
-Before it caused so much pain.
-[sniffles]

1426
01:22:44.600 --> 01:22:47.880
[Sarah] With or without Charlie.
you will be fine.

1427
01:22:48.400 --> 01:22:49.920
You will find yourself again.

1428
01:22:51.720 --> 01:22:54.640
But I just don't want you to give up on it
before it's over.

1429
01:22:57.120 --> 01:22:58.600
Charlie loves you.

1430
01:22:59.400 --> 01:23:00.720
The real you.

1431
01:23:05.080 --> 01:23:06.120
It's too late.

1432
01:23:06.200 --> 01:23:07.600
No. it's not.

1433
01:23:08.440 --> 01:23:13.240
[sighs] Love isn't destiny or fate
or some kind of cosmic force.

1434
01:23:13.320 --> 01:23:14.800
Love is a choice.

1435
01:23:14.880 --> 01:23:17.640
It's a choice every day.

1436
01:23:17.720 --> 01:23:20.360
and you can…
you can lean towards it or away from it.

1437
01:23:20.440 --> 01:23:22.640
and you have always leant towards it.

1438
01:23:22.720 --> 01:23:23.920
That is just

1439
01:23:25.200 --> 01:23:26.480
who you are.

1440
01:23:29.600 --> 01:23:31.800
I think that's who Charlie is as well.

1441
01:23:45.040 --> 01:23:47.120
I did warn you it'd be boring.

1442
01:23:47.640 --> 01:23:50.720
He just goes round and round.

1443
01:23:50.800 --> 01:23:53.200
-He's happy you're here though.
-I know he is.

1444
01:23:55.680 --> 01:23:57.240
You're very cute.

1445
01:23:57.800 --> 01:23:59.320
For a straight couple.

1446
01:24:00.480 --> 01:24:01.960
What are you talking about?

1447
01:24:02.480 --> 01:24:03.840
Since when are we straight?

1448
01:24:04.440 --> 01:24:05.440
[chuckles]

1449
01:24:05.880 --> 01:24:08.320
I'm surprised
you didn't notice with Michael.

1450
01:24:08.400 --> 01:24:11.720
He's always going on about Pedro Pascal
or whatever.

1451
01:24:11.800 --> 01:24:13.120
But what about you?

1452
01:24:13.640 --> 01:24:16.040
-You know I'm asexual. don't you?
-No.

1453
01:24:16.560 --> 01:24:20.320
-Oh. Could've sworn I told you that.
-[chuckles incredulously]

1454
01:24:21.560 --> 01:24:23.440
I mean.
that actually makes a lot of sense.

1455
01:24:23.520 --> 01:24:26.760
Every time I talk about men.
you make this really grossed-out face.

1456
01:24:29.240 --> 01:24:31.400
But… [hesitates]

1457
01:24:31.480 --> 01:24:33.720
This is gonna sound really horrible. but

1458
01:24:35.440 --> 01:24:36.800
why are you together?

1459
01:24:37.320 --> 01:24:39.160
You're. like. basically opposites.

1460
01:24:39.920 --> 01:24:43.080
We're together because we're together.

1461
01:24:44.160 --> 01:24:46.520
Because we're Tori and Michael.

1462
01:24:47.040 --> 01:24:49.840
and… we're happy together.

1463
01:24:50.640 --> 01:24:51.960
That's all there is.

1464
01:24:53.640 --> 01:24:56.200
Whether it's romance
or friendship or whatever.

1465
01:24:56.280 --> 01:24:58.080
that's everyone else's problem.

1466
01:25:00.560 --> 01:25:04.280
Maybe our together isn't the same
as your together

1467
01:25:04.800 --> 01:25:06.840
or the normal sort of together.

1468
01:25:07.960 --> 01:25:12.200
but it's ours. and we're happy with it.

1469
01:25:14.200 --> 01:25:16.480
And maybe that will change in the future.

1470
01:25:17.400 --> 01:25:18.600
Maybe it won't.

1471
01:25:20.160 --> 01:25:21.480
But. for now.

1472
01:25:22.320 --> 01:25:23.480
we're here.

1473
01:25:24.360 --> 01:25:26.760
and this is what it is.

1474
01:25:29.560 --> 01:25:32.280
-We're here. and we're alive and whatever.
-[chuckles]

1475
01:25:32.360 --> 01:25:34.040
[coach] Okay. great. Well done.

1476
01:25:34.120 --> 01:25:36.160
[gentle music playing]

1477
01:25:39.920 --> 01:25:42.320
-[posh voice] Hello.
-[funny voice] Hello.

1478
01:25:44.680 --> 01:25:47.200
[chuckles. normal voice] How was it?

1479
01:25:47.280 --> 01:25:50.360
-[Michael] It was good. yeah.
-[both chuckling]

1480
01:26:01.000 --> 01:26:03.000
[music fades]

1481
01:26:07.360 --> 01:26:08.560
[exhales sharply]

1482
01:26:12.640 --> 01:26:15.680
[sentimental music playing]

1483
01:26:30.480 --> 01:26:31.560
[chuckles]

1484
01:26:38.240 --> 01:26:39.680
[exhales sharply]

1485
01:26:48.880 --> 01:26:50.360
[music building]

1486
01:26:55.000 --> 01:26:56.280
[sighs]

1487
01:26:59.520 --> 01:27:00.880
[sighs]

1488
01:27:20.480 --> 01:27:23.120
-[gentle music playing]
-[sighs]

1489
01:27:35.160 --> 01:27:36.320
Shit!

1490
01:27:37.200 --> 01:27:39.440
[indie pop ballad instrumental playing]

1491
01:28:03.480 --> 01:28:05.800
-[music fades]
-I got the photos.

1492
01:28:06.640 --> 01:28:09.560
Well. obviously. Here I am.

1493
01:28:10.080 --> 01:28:12.360
Genuinely the most embarrassing thing
I've ever done.

1494
01:28:13.520 --> 01:28:15.760
I'm the one
who took a billion photos of you.

1495
01:28:15.840 --> 01:28:19.160
[chuckles softly] I guess we're both
pretty embarrassing. then.

1496
01:28:19.680 --> 01:28:20.800
[Nick chuckles softly]

1497
01:28:23.600 --> 01:28:25.600
-I really missed you.
-[sniffles]

1498
01:28:27.240 --> 01:28:28.560
I missed you too.

1499
01:28:33.800 --> 01:28:36.600
Everyone thinks
teenage relationships don't last.

1500
01:28:37.880 --> 01:28:39.920
I never really thought that about us.

1501
01:28:42.520 --> 01:28:43.520
Me neither.

1502
01:28:45.800 --> 01:28:48.920
Ever since we met. I… can feel it.

1503
01:28:51.320 --> 01:28:52.480
We're different.

1504
01:28:53.720 --> 01:28:55.160
[Nick chuckles softly]

1505
01:28:58.000 --> 01:28:59.920
But we stopped talking to each other.

1506
01:29:00.640 --> 01:29:01.640
[sighs]

1507
01:29:02.800 --> 01:29:05.000
I couldn't help you like you helped me.

1508
01:29:05.080 --> 01:29:06.280
[Nick inhales deeply]

1509
01:29:07.840 --> 01:29:08.920
You did.

1510
01:29:11.080 --> 01:29:13.760
You're just so good
at saying how you feel. I…

1511
01:29:14.560 --> 01:29:17.720
I barely know what I feel half the time.

1512
01:29:21.720 --> 01:29:22.800
I never…

1513
01:29:25.320 --> 01:29:27.080
I never knew what to do

1514
01:29:28.120 --> 01:29:29.640
when I felt sad.

1515
01:29:33.840 --> 01:29:35.400
I just know I love you.

1516
01:29:39.680 --> 01:29:40.880
Is that okay?

1517
01:29:42.360 --> 01:29:43.800
[Charlie exhales sharply]

1518
01:29:45.920 --> 01:29:47.440
We look after each other.

1519
01:29:48.240 --> 01:29:49.240
don't we?

1520
01:29:53.560 --> 01:29:55.080
Always. [chuckles softly]

1521
01:29:57.280 --> 01:29:59.200
[indie music playing]

1522
01:30:01.200 --> 01:30:02.720
[sparks crackling]

1523
01:30:06.200 --> 01:30:08.600
[inaudible]

1524
01:30:08.680 --> 01:30:13.600
♪ There I saw you standing
Must've been a holy light ♪

1525
01:30:13.680 --> 01:30:16.520
♪ 'Cause I can't see and I can't feel ♪

1526
01:30:16.600 --> 01:30:19.920
♪ But the color in your eyes is saying ♪

1527
01:30:20.000 --> 01:30:22.000
♪ If my dreams come up empty ♪

1528
01:30:22.080 --> 01:30:25.040
♪ And I wash up on the shore ♪

1529
01:30:25.120 --> 01:30:30.920
♪ You would find me at the beach
In every life. through every door ♪

1530
01:30:31.000 --> 01:30:36.440
♪ With a boom box at your father's
Walking with you at the morgue ♪

1531
01:30:36.520 --> 01:30:42.160
♪ You don't have to search when I know
Everything you're looking for ♪

1532
01:30:42.240 --> 01:30:45.800
♪ Oh. and we could talk about it ♪

1533
01:30:45.880 --> 01:30:48.000
♪ Or just stare at the wall ♪

1534
01:30:48.080 --> 01:30:54.040
♪ But I think that you know better than
What they think they call ♪

1535
01:30:54.120 --> 01:30:56.920
♪ A luminary. no one ♪

1536
01:30:57.000 --> 01:30:59.200
♪ Is all they'll ever be ♪

1537
01:30:59.920 --> 01:31:02.400
♪ And how could you be no one ♪

1538
01:31:02.480 --> 01:31:06.680
♪ When you're everything to me? ♪

1539
01:31:10.040 --> 01:31:12.720
♪ You're everything to me ♪

1540
01:31:15.520 --> 01:31:18.400
♪ You're everything to me ♪

1541
01:31:21.400 --> 01:31:27.360
-♪ You're everything to me ♪
-[Nick moaning]

1542
01:31:28.720 --> 01:31:32.360
[singer vocalizing]

1543
01:31:32.440 --> 01:31:34.360
[both breathing heavily]

1544
01:31:44.840 --> 01:31:45.960
I love you.

1545
01:31:46.600 --> 01:31:47.760
I love you.

1546
01:31:49.760 --> 01:31:50.840
[Nick chuckles]

1547
01:32:03.720 --> 01:32:05.720
[music fades]

1548
01:32:05.800 --> 01:32:07.160
[Imogen giggling]

1549
01:32:07.240 --> 01:32:09.400
-Come on.
-[Sahar] There's a step!

1550
01:32:10.080 --> 01:32:13.000
-[Sahar] Watch this step.
-[Imogen] We're gonna be late for prom!

1551
01:32:13.080 --> 01:32:14.640
[electronic music playing]

1552
01:32:14.720 --> 01:32:16.280
-[Sahar] Guys!
-[both] We're here!

1553
01:32:16.360 --> 01:32:18.160
There you are! You need some drinks.

1554
01:32:18.240 --> 01:32:19.840
Yes. please.

1555
01:32:19.920 --> 01:32:22.000
-[screams playfully]
-[all chattering happily]

1556
01:32:22.080 --> 01:32:24.720
-Ha-ha! My evil laugh.
-Oh wow.

1557
01:32:24.800 --> 01:32:27.320
-You gonna have a shot?
-[Tara] Darcy!

1558
01:32:27.400 --> 01:32:28.800
Oh my God.

1559
01:32:28.880 --> 01:32:29.920
-Oh-oh!
-Aww!

1560
01:32:30.000 --> 01:32:31.680
[Tara] They're back together!

1561
01:32:32.600 --> 01:32:34.040
Yeah! He loves you!

1562
01:32:34.120 --> 01:32:35.400
[all] Aww!

1563
01:32:36.600 --> 01:32:39.040
-Cheers. cheers. cheers. cheers!
-[all cheering]

1564
01:32:39.120 --> 01:32:41.920
[Tara] To forever! Whoo!

1565
01:32:42.000 --> 01:32:43.760
[happy squeals. cheers]

1566
01:32:43.840 --> 01:32:46.840
♪ 'Cause the good shit in life
Is always free… ♪

1567
01:32:48.280 --> 01:32:49.560
You're dancing.

1568
01:32:52.080 --> 01:32:55.200
♪ Take a look around
Tell me what you see ♪

1569
01:32:56.480 --> 01:32:58.240
♪ 'Cause the good shit… ♪

1570
01:32:58.320 --> 01:32:59.680
-Sir. come on.
-[Nick] Come on.

1571
01:32:59.760 --> 01:33:01.280
[Sahar] You know you wanna.

1572
01:33:01.360 --> 01:33:03.760
-Go on. Do something.
-[Tao] Go on!

1573
01:33:03.840 --> 01:33:06.560
-[all cheering]
-[Sahar] Thank you!

1574
01:33:09.000 --> 01:33:11.640
Tara and Darcy.
what does the future hold for you?

1575
01:33:11.720 --> 01:33:15.520
-We are going Interrailing.
-We're gonna see the world!

1576
01:33:15.600 --> 01:33:18.440
-♪ Show me what you want from me… ♪
-[Darcy laughing]

1577
01:33:20.000 --> 01:33:21.560
Isaac and Imogen.

1578
01:33:21.640 --> 01:33:23.840
I'm gonna write a book
about all of you lot.

1579
01:33:23.920 --> 01:33:26.840
Hmm. I think I wanna be.
like. a lawyer or. like. a CEO.

1580
01:33:26.920 --> 01:33:28.400
-Cheese.
-[Tao] Oh!

1581
01:33:29.040 --> 01:33:30.040
Oh my God.

1582
01:33:30.120 --> 01:33:33.880
Oh. so the band didn't work out.
but I'm gonna go solo.

1583
01:33:33.960 --> 01:33:35.720
-[Tao] Solo.
-Oh yeah!

1584
01:33:36.400 --> 01:33:37.880
-Yeah!
-[both giggling]

1585
01:33:37.960 --> 01:33:39.000
[Sahar] Mm-hmm!

1586
01:33:39.080 --> 01:33:40.280
The future?

1587
01:33:41.520 --> 01:33:42.680
[both] Um…

1588
01:33:42.760 --> 01:33:43.920
Marriage?

1589
01:33:44.000 --> 01:33:45.200
Tao!

1590
01:33:45.920 --> 01:33:47.640
[electronic music continues]

1591
01:33:47.720 --> 01:33:48.800
-[giggling]
-[Nick] Hey!

1592
01:33:48.880 --> 01:33:50.000
No!

1593
01:33:52.560 --> 01:33:55.640
[Tao] Hey.
What does the future hold for you?

1594
01:33:55.720 --> 01:33:58.680
I don't know.
Probably nothing and then death.

1595
01:33:58.760 --> 01:34:01.560
[whooping. laughter]

1596
01:34:02.920 --> 01:34:04.160
Round there.

1597
01:34:04.240 --> 01:34:07.000
♪ 'Cause the good shit in life
Is always free ♪

1598
01:34:07.080 --> 01:34:08.920
-[all cheering]
-♪ Is free ♪

1599
01:34:09.000 --> 01:34:11.680
And finally. Elle.

1600
01:34:11.760 --> 01:34:14.080
[indie music playing]

1601
01:34:14.160 --> 01:34:15.680
What's your plans for the future?

1602
01:34:18.400 --> 01:34:21.320
I'm going to Berlin to be an artist.

1603
01:34:23.160 --> 01:34:24.320
[video camera beeps]

1604
01:34:25.480 --> 01:34:26.760
One last dance?

1605
01:34:28.880 --> 01:34:30.160
Let's make it a good one.

1606
01:34:35.080 --> 01:34:37.280
Oh. Thank you.

1607
01:34:40.440 --> 01:34:44.080
♪ I might've been sick
Then well. then sick some more ♪

1608
01:34:47.680 --> 01:34:49.960
♪ I might be prouder of me… ♪

1609
01:34:51.280 --> 01:34:52.600
[Tao sighs emotionally]

1610
01:34:52.680 --> 01:34:55.560
♪ Than I ever have been ♪

1611
01:34:56.280 --> 01:34:58.880
♪ I've been learning 'bout letting go ♪

1612
01:35:01.760 --> 01:35:06.840
♪ How to do it without my claws
Scratching the surfaces ♪

1613
01:35:07.480 --> 01:35:10.520
♪ I've been learning 'bout wasting time ♪

1614
01:35:10.600 --> 01:35:12.720
♪ And closing some doors ♪

1615
01:35:13.800 --> 01:35:16.880
♪ Hoping to open more down the line ♪

1616
01:35:29.640 --> 01:35:33.960
♪ I knew from miles away
That I would detonate ♪

1617
01:35:35.520 --> 01:35:38.680
♪ I tried some magic tricks
To skip my fate… ♪

1618
01:35:38.760 --> 01:35:41.360
[Tara] Guys. Guys. look! Look!

1619
01:35:41.440 --> 01:35:43.200
[Mr. Farouk and Mr. Ajayi laughing]

1620
01:35:43.280 --> 01:35:45.960
[both] Oh. oh. oh. oh!

1621
01:35:47.280 --> 01:35:48.720
[Mr. Ajayi] Oh? [chuckling]

1622
01:35:51.240 --> 01:35:52.160
We should do that.

1623
01:35:52.240 --> 01:35:53.840
-Thank you.
-[Mr. Farouk] Mm-hmm.

1624
01:35:53.920 --> 01:35:57.160
-[Mr. Ajayi] Ooh!
-[all] Aaah! [laughter]

1625
01:36:06.440 --> 01:36:07.840
[Tao sighs heavily]

1626
01:36:09.600 --> 01:36:10.680
You okay?

1627
01:36:16.080 --> 01:36:17.080
No.

1628
01:36:21.480 --> 01:36:23.280
It's not as sad as you think though.

1629
01:36:24.720 --> 01:36:28.080
It's not like we don't love each other.
and whatever happens.

1630
01:36:28.160 --> 01:36:31.000
whether we're together or not.
whether she's near or far.

1631
01:36:31.080 --> 01:36:33.440
I know she'll always be in my life.

1632
01:36:35.520 --> 01:36:36.640
You know?

1633
01:36:36.720 --> 01:36:37.720
Yeah.

1634
01:36:38.160 --> 01:36:40.160
[Tao] I mean. all of us.

1635
01:36:41.120 --> 01:36:42.520
The exact relationships may change.

1636
01:36:42.560 --> 01:36:45.200
and people may fall
in and out of touch. but

1637
01:36:46.360 --> 01:36:50.000
the love that connects us
will never break.

1638
01:36:51.600 --> 01:36:52.760
We built it.

1639
01:36:54.240 --> 01:36:55.400
And it built us.

1640
01:36:59.080 --> 01:37:00.760
[Nick inhales deeply]

1641
01:37:05.080 --> 01:37:06.520
-[chuckles softly]
-Crisp?

1642
01:37:06.600 --> 01:37:07.880
[both chuckle]

1643
01:37:07.960 --> 01:37:09.640
Yeah. Yeah. go on.

1644
01:37:10.720 --> 01:37:12.240
That's ready salted.

1645
01:37:12.840 --> 01:37:13.840
Okay.

1646
01:37:14.280 --> 01:37:15.600
-Cheers.
-[clicks tongue]

1647
01:37:17.160 --> 01:37:19.960
♪ It's okay. it's okay ♪

1648
01:37:20.040 --> 01:37:22.800
♪ Make mistakes. make mistakes ♪

1649
01:37:22.880 --> 01:37:24.920
♪ It's okay. it's okay ♪

1650
01:37:25.680 --> 01:37:28.400
♪ Make mistakes. make mistakes ♪

1651
01:37:28.480 --> 01:37:31.200
-♪ It's okay. it's okay… ♪
-[Imogen squealing happily]

1652
01:37:32.120 --> 01:37:33.640
-Hi.
-[Nick] Hello.

1653
01:37:35.600 --> 01:37:37.200
-Wanna race?
-Yeah?

1654
01:37:37.280 --> 01:37:39.720
-♪ Make mistakes. make mistakes ♪
-[Charlie] Come on!

1655
01:37:39.800 --> 01:37:42.480
♪ It's okay. it's okay ♪

1656
01:37:42.560 --> 01:37:45.600
♪ Make mistakes. make mistakes ♪

1657
01:37:45.680 --> 01:37:48.200
♪ It's okay. it's okay ♪

1658
01:37:48.280 --> 01:37:50.000
-♪ Make mistakes… ♪
-[Charlie] No!

1659
01:37:50.080 --> 01:37:51.680
-[Nick] Yes!
-[Charlie] No!

1660
01:37:51.760 --> 01:37:53.680
♪ It's okay. it's okay ♪

1661
01:37:53.760 --> 01:37:56.480
-♪ Make mistakes. make mistakes ♪
-[Charlie giggling]

1662
01:37:56.560 --> 01:37:59.840
♪ Make mistakes. make mistakes ♪

1663
01:38:02.400 --> 01:38:03.880
-[music fades]
-[door closes]

1664
01:38:03.960 --> 01:38:06.120
-It's smaller than I remember.
-[Nick] Yeah.

1665
01:38:07.200 --> 01:38:09.680
Feels like no one's come in here
since we did.

1666
01:38:11.600 --> 01:38:13.520
[Charlie] They should put a plaque
on the wall.

1667
01:38:13.600 --> 01:38:16.400
"This is where Nick
and Charlie had their first kiss."

1668
01:38:24.920 --> 01:38:25.920
[chuckles softly]

1669
01:38:34.040 --> 01:38:35.320
[Nick groans softly]

1670
01:38:37.880 --> 01:38:39.840
-I feel old.
-[Nick] Hmm.

1671
01:38:41.560 --> 01:38:42.760
We are not old.

1672
01:38:43.280 --> 01:38:45.200
Last time we were in here. we were babies.

1673
01:38:46.360 --> 01:38:48.240
Yeah. I didn't know anything.

1674
01:38:48.760 --> 01:38:51.840
Except I wanted to kiss you so bad
I thought I was gonna die.

1675
01:38:52.360 --> 01:38:54.920
-I still feel like that quite a lot.
-Do you?

1676
01:38:56.200 --> 01:38:58.600
Yeah. Yeah.
You'd better kiss me so I don't die.

1677
01:38:58.680 --> 01:39:00.560
I wouldn't want that to happen.

1678
01:39:06.600 --> 01:39:07.920
[Nick sighs]

1679
01:39:10.320 --> 01:39:12.920
So I'm gonna go to uni.

1680
01:39:13.000 --> 01:39:15.560
and then you're gonna go to uni in a year.

1681
01:39:16.200 --> 01:39:20.120
I'll come back every other weekend.
or you can come to Leeds.

1682
01:39:21.480 --> 01:39:23.080
It's only a few years.

1683
01:39:23.600 --> 01:39:26.400
Really not that long compared to…

1684
01:39:27.840 --> 01:39:29.560
The rest of our lives?

1685
01:39:31.080 --> 01:39:32.080
Yeah.

1686
01:39:32.440 --> 01:39:33.640
[Charlie chuckles softly]

1687
01:39:35.120 --> 01:39:37.520
I could never imagine any of that
till I met you.

1688
01:39:39.600 --> 01:39:40.600
And now?

1689
01:39:41.760 --> 01:39:43.040
Now I can see it.

1690
01:39:44.720 --> 01:39:47.880
-[Nick chuckles softly]
-[gentle music playing]

1691
01:40:03.280 --> 01:40:04.440
[both chuckle softly]

1692
01:40:08.320 --> 01:40:09.800
[Charlie sighs]

1693
01:40:17.680 --> 01:40:19.080
[music fades]

1694
01:40:19.160 --> 01:40:20.400
[Charlie chuckles]

1695
01:40:20.480 --> 01:40:23.080
-Oh. don't… don't delete it.
-I'm not going to.

1696
01:40:24.120 --> 01:40:26.960
[chuckles] Can I use it as my wallpaper?

1697
01:40:27.040 --> 01:40:29.760
What. and replace the picture
of Henry and Nellie?

1698
01:40:30.440 --> 01:40:33.376
-You really love me more than your dogs?
-Mm. yeah. that's going a bit far.

1699
01:40:33.400 --> 01:40:34.400
[Charlie scoffs]

1700
01:40:34.440 --> 01:40:37.880
Okay. fine. I love you more than my dogs.

1701
01:40:38.400 --> 01:40:40.760
I love you more than anyone. actually.

1702
01:40:42.120 --> 01:40:43.160
Is that weird?

1703
01:40:43.680 --> 01:40:44.960
[Charlie chuckles softly]

1704
01:40:45.040 --> 01:40:46.400
I'm only 18.

1705
01:40:47.640 --> 01:40:48.880
I'm weird too.

1706
01:40:52.080 --> 01:40:54.040
[indie pop music playing]

1707
01:41:01.000 --> 01:41:04.080
♪ Walked in straight away
And slammed the door last night… ♪

1708
01:41:04.160 --> 01:41:09.400
-[Darcy squealing excitedly]
-[both giggling]

1709
01:41:09.480 --> 01:41:12.160
[announcer] The train will be arriving
in 25 minutes.

1710
01:41:12.240 --> 01:41:14.000
-♪ With the TV on… ♪
-[both squeal excitedly]

1711
01:41:16.280 --> 01:41:18.640
-[Imogen giggles. squeals]
-[Sahar] You made it!

1712
01:41:18.720 --> 01:41:21.440
-[Imogen] I'm so excited!
-Aww. thank you for coming!

1713
01:41:21.520 --> 01:41:24.880
-I know. I've got to go on.
-Go on. You're gonna be amazing!

1714
01:41:25.920 --> 01:41:28.360
[crowd cheering. whooping]

1715
01:41:28.440 --> 01:41:31.280
-Who's ready to rock?!
-[crowd cheering. whistling]

1716
01:41:32.280 --> 01:41:35.800
-♪ Listen. it's been a long. long year ♪
-[cell phone buzzing]

1717
01:41:35.880 --> 01:41:38.920
♪ I think we should go
And get you out of here… ♪

1718
01:41:39.000 --> 01:41:40.560
-Hi.
-Are you sitting down?

1719
01:41:40.640 --> 01:41:41.720
I'm at the library.

1720
01:41:42.440 --> 01:41:43.440
Okay. incoming.

1721
01:41:45.160 --> 01:41:47.040
-Oh my God!
-Shh!

1722
01:41:47.800 --> 01:41:49.120
♪ Pack up all your shit ♪

1723
01:41:49.200 --> 01:41:51.280
-♪ And put it in the back ♪
-Well done.

1724
01:41:51.800 --> 01:41:54.520
-♪ Maybe the miles can make up… ♪
-[typing]

1725
01:41:54.600 --> 01:41:56.120
[Isaac] Don't look.

1726
01:41:56.640 --> 01:41:58.920
I wanna be in the acknowledgements
of your book.

1727
01:41:59.000 --> 01:42:00.640
We can talk about it.

1728
01:42:03.600 --> 01:42:06.560
♪ Cruising 95
Like we got nothing to lose ♪

1729
01:42:06.640 --> 01:42:10.880
♪ I'm praying to the headlights
Like I prayed to you… ♪

1730
01:42:10.960 --> 01:42:12.240
[man speaking German]

1731
01:42:14.600 --> 01:42:16.360
-[in English] Hi.
-Thank you for coming.

1732
01:42:16.440 --> 01:42:18.280
Of course. So good to see you.

1733
01:42:18.360 --> 01:42:21.280
